	(24,'Image Post','831-autosave-v1',NULL,NULL,'[dropcap style=\"\"]Z[/dropcap]oey reflections just here are occasioned by the<a title=\"Hood\" href=\"#\"> circumstance</a> that after we were all seated at the table, and I was preparing to hear some good stories about whaling to my no small surprise, nearly every man maintained a profound silence. And not only that, but they looked embarrassed. Here were a set of sea-dogs, many of whom without the slightest bashfulness had boarded great whales on the high seas entire strangers to them and duelled them dead without winkingand yet, here they sat at a social breakfast table all of the same calling, all of kindred tastes looking round as sheepishly at each other as<strong><em>the Green Mountains</em></strong>though they had never been out of sight of some sheepfold among. A curious sight these bashful bears, these timid warrior whalemen.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_1473\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"1100\"]<img class=\"wp-image-1473 size-fit\" src=\"/storage/images/media_items/old_images/2014/10/aaa43.png\" alt=\"sleek_post28_00_01\" width=\"1100\" height=\"825\" /> The Dark Sea, 2014[/caption]\n\n[separator size=\"small\" center=\"false\"]\n\nThey say that men who have seen the world, thereby become quite at ease in manner, quite self-possessed in company. Not always, though Ledyard the great New England traveller and Mungo Park, the Scotch one of all men, they possessed the least assurance in the parlor. Perhaps the mere crossing of Siberia in a sledge drawn by dogs as Ledyard did, or the taking a long solitary walk on an empty stomach. In the negro heart of Africa, which was the sum of poor <strong><em>Mungo\'s performances</em></strong> this kind of travel, I say, may not be the very best mode of attaining a high social polish. Still, for the most part, that sort of thing is to be had anywhere. There now is your insular city of<strong><em> the Manhattoes</em></strong>, belted round by wharves as Indian isles by coral reefs?commerce surrounds it with her surf. Right and left, the streets take you water-ward.\n\n[separator size=\"small\" center=\"false\"]\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1324 size-fit\" src=\"/storage/images/media_items/old_images/2014/10/aaa43.png\" alt=\"sleek_post16_00_00_02\" width=\"1100\" height=\"619\" />\n\n[separator size=\"small\" center=\"false\"]\n\nThese reflections just here are occasioned by the circumstance that after we were all seated at the table, nearly every man maintained a profound silence. And not only that, but they looked embarrassed. Here were a set of sea-dogs, many of whom without the slightest bashfulness had boarded great whales <a title=\"Ooze\" href=\"#\">entire strangers to them</a>and duelled them dead without winking and yet, here they sat at a social breakfast table all of the same calling, all of kindred tastes looking round as sheepishly at each other as though they had never been out of sight of some sheepfold among <em><strong>the Green Mountains</strong></em>. A curious sight these bashful bears, these timid warrior whalemen. Extreme downtown is <a title=\"The Battery\" href=\"#\">the battery</a>, where that noble mole is washed by waves, and cooled by breezes, which a few hours previous were out of sight of land.\n\n[separator size=\"small\" center=\"false\"]\n\n<em>Models:<strong>Anna Moose</strong>, <strong>Sarah</strong> &amp; <strong>Hanna Jones</strong></em>',NULL,NULL,9,'2015-08-24 10:11:20','2015-08-24 10:11:20',1,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/2015/08/24/831-autosave-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(25,'Standard Post with Excerpt','741-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'[caption id=\"attachment_939\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"1100\"]<img class=\"wp-image-939 size-fit\" src=\"/storage/images/media_items/old_images/2014/10/aaa43.png\" alt=\"sleek_post05_00\" width=\"1100\" height=\"929\" /> Connie &amp; Clark, 2014[/caption]\n\n[dropcap style=\"\"]K[/dropcap]ate was a wondrous sight. The wood was green as mosses of the Icy Glen; the trees stood high and haughty, feeling their living sap; the industrious earth beneath was as a weaver\'s loom, with a <a title=\"Picture\" href=\"#\">gorgeous carpet</a> on it, whereof the ground-vine tendrils formed the warp and woof, and the living flowers the figures. [highlighted_text]All the trees, with all their laden branches; all the shrubs, and ferns, and grasses; the message carrying air; all these unceasingly were active. Through the lacings of the leaves, the great sun seemed a flying shuttle weaving the unwearied verdure. Oh, busy weaver! [/highlighted_text]unseen weaver whither flows the fabric. What palace may it deck? wherefore all these ceaseless toilings. One single word with thee the shuttle flies the figures float from forth the loom; the freshet-rushing carpet for ever slides away.\n\n[separator size=\"small\" center=\"false\"]\n\n[highlighted_p boxed=\"false\"]The weaver-god he weaves and by that weaving is he deafened, that he hears no mortal voice. That humming we who look on the loom are deafened. Only when we escape it shall we hear the thousand voices that speak through it. For even so it is in all material <em><strong>Factories</strong></em>. The spoken words that are inaudible among <strong><em>the Flying Spindles</em></strong>. Those same words are plainly heard without the walls.[/highlighted_p]\n\n[separator size=\"small\" center=\"false\"]\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_679\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1100\"]<img class=\"wp-image-679 size-fit\" src=\"/storage/images/media_items/old_images/2014/10/aaa43.png\" alt=\"Title 3 - 10011\" width=\"1100\" height=\"734\" /> Connie &amp; Clark, 2014[/caption]\n\n[separator size=\"small\" center=\"false\"]\n<h2>In Short</h2>\nCurtains to <a title=\"The Image\" href=\"#\">the window</a>, and that the street being very narrow, the house opposite commanded a plain view into the room, and observing more and more the indecorous figure that made staving about with little else but his hat and boots on. I begged him as well as I could, to accelerate his toilet somewhat, and particularly to get into his pantaloons as soon as possible. [highlighted_text]He complied, and then proceeded to wash himself at that time in the morning any Christian would have washed his face to my amazement contented himself with <a title=\"The Artist\" href=\"#\">restricting</a> his ablutions to his chest, arms, and hands. Then donned his waistcoat, and taking up a piece of hard soap.[/highlighted_text] On the wash-stand centre table dipped it into water and commenced lathering his face. I was watching to see where he kept his razor, when behold he takes the harpoon from the bed corner and striding up to the bit of mirror against the wall begins a vigorous scraping. Rather harpooning of his cheeks.\n\n<em>Production <strong>Connie </strong>&amp;<strong> Clark</strong></em>',NULL,NULL,9,'2015-08-24 11:36:52','2015-08-24 11:36:52',1,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/2015/08/24/741-revision-v1/',1,1,1,1,0,NULL,NULL),
	(26,'10 Reasons to return to education this September','10-reasons-study-september',NULL,NULL,'It\'s the start of the new academic year and thousands return to education, and you can too- by studying at home with Open Study College\n\nIf you need that extra push to boost your skills, then why not take a look at our 10 reasons to study with us today?\n<h2>Affordable education</h2>\n\nYou can boost your skills for less than you think. We understand that cost can often be a barrier to education. However with our competitive course prices and a flexible monthly payment plan which lets you spread the cost of your course into low monthly instalments ? investing in your future is easy and stress-free!\n<h2>Award-winning tutor support </h2>\n\nExperts in their fields, our tutors are on hand to ensure you progress with ease and confidence with your studies. From offering their advice and feedback or simply giving you that little push to get you started ? they?re just an email away!\n<h2>A CV that stands out from the crowd </h2>\nOnce you?ve earned those new skills, we?ll help you to create the perfect CV to show them off and really grab employers? attention.\n<h2>Exclusive discounts </h2>\nEnjoy the perks of becoming a student and make your money go further. You?ll receive a free NUS extra card once you?ve enrolled which lets you enjoy discounts across your favourite brands.\n\n<h2>Trusted, Independent qualifications </h2>\n\nBench-marked against the highest of industry standards, our awards will open up doors to your dream career. All accredited by independent awarding bodies, you can feel confident you are studying for a qualification you can trust.\n\n<h2>Education without the classroom </h2>\nWith no classes to attend, you can say goodbye to venturing out on a cold wet winter evening and enjoy studying all from the comfort of your own home.\n<h2>Boost your salary </h2>\nThe more qualifications you have, the more money you could be earning. Qualifications are often what 