	(81,'How to achieve your goals','how-to-achieve-your-goals',NULL,NULL,'Everyone starts a new project filled with enthusiasm, but if you really want to see it through to the end and achieve your goals you need to work at it.  So here are a few tips:\n\n<h2>Set specific goals</h2>\nMake the effort to set goals. Do this regularly in order to make adjustments and improve on them.\n<h2>Write them down</h2>\nHow often have you said you?re going to do something next year and then forgotten all about it?\n\nWhen you write down your goals it will make it real. You can?t then convince yourself that you never said it. It should then make you want to achieve them.\n<h2>Are your goals S.M.A.R.T?</h2>\nUnless your goals are realistic and measurable then it?s doubtful that you?ll achieve what you want to. So make them S.M.A.R.T\n\nYour goals need to be:\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong>S</strong>pecific</li>\n 	<li><strong>M</strong>easurable</li>\n 	<li><strong>A</strong>chievable</li>\n 	<li><strong>R</strong>esults-focused</li>\n 	<li><strong>T</strong>ime-bound</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Can they be broken down into small goals?</h2>\nCreate goals for every month. They can be broken down into weekly and then daily goals. You?ll then know what you need to do every day in order to achieve your main monthly objective.\n<h2>Don?t give up</h2>\nDon?t say you can?t complete any goals. Push yourself further so you can. When you have completed your goal you will then feel proud.\n\nNow you know how to achieve your goals, make this year your year!',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-06 13:09:04','2017-06-07 15:33:07',2,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=4315',1,1,1,2,0,NULL,NULL),
	(82,'How to achieve your goals','4315-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'It?s time to start thinking about what you want to achieve in the new year. But if you\'re like most people you\'ll have given up on your New Year resolutions before you\'ve even managed to pack away the Christmas decorations. So here are a few tips to help?\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol>\n	<li><strong>Set goals</strong></li>\n</ol>\nMake the effort to set goals. Do this regularly in order to make adjustments and improve on them.\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start=\"2\">\n	<li><strong>Write them down</strong></li>\n</ol>\nHow often have you said you?re going to do something next year and then forgotten all about it?\n\nWhen you write down your goals it will make it real. You can?t then convince yourself that you never said it. It should then make you want to achieve them.\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start=\"3\">\n	<li><strong>Are your goals S.M.A.R.T?</strong></li>\n</ol>\nUnless your goals are realistic and measurable then it?s doubtful that you?ll achieve what you want to. So make them S.M.A.R.T\n\nYour goals need to be:\n\n&nbsp;\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>S</strong>pecific</li>\n	<li><strong>M</strong>easurable</li>\n	<li><strong>A</strong>chievable</li>\n	<li><strong>R</strong>esults-focused</li>\n	<li><strong>T</strong>ime-bound</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n<ol start=\"4\">\n	<li><strong>Can they be broken down into small goals?</strong></li>\n</ol>\nCreate goals for every month. They can be broken down into weekly and then daily goals. You?ll then know what you need to do every day in order to achieve your main monthly objective.\n\n&nbsp;\n<ol start=\"5\">\n	<li><strong>Don?t give up</strong></li>\n</ol>\nDon?t say you can?t complete any goals. Push yourself further so you can. When you have completed your goal you will then feel proud.',NULL,NULL,9,'2015-12-17 09:15:57','2015-12-17 09:15:57',1,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/2015/12/17/4315-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
