	(98,'How to make a study plan','make-study-plan',NULL,NULL,'Distance learning helps you learn when it\'s convenient but if you want to gain the qualification you need, then you\'ll need to manage your time effectively. That\'s why you should make a study plan.\n\n<h2>What is a study plan?</h2>\nIt is an organised schedule that you can use to determine study times, learning objectives and goals. You can dedicate certain days and times for studying around all of your other commitments. Determination and self-discipline will be needed to achieve success.\n<h2>Create a table with your current activities</h2>\nMake a one week time table and note:\n<ul>\n	<li>The daily activities you partake in</li>\n	<li>When you are at work/school</li>\n	<li>When you are at home and with family</li>\n	<li>When you eat and sleep</li>\n</ul>\nOnce you have done this, look for times you can dedicate your time to studying. These days and times may be consistent throughout every week.\n<h2>Develop a schedule</h2>\nFrom your current timetable, make a mark in your planner and calendar of all the available days and times devoted to studying. Make sure you block out your studying times on your calendar. You should do this by making it visible and bold, so you don?t forget it. You should also add the subject you are studying, in case you have more than one course to study. This will help you devote enough time to each.\n<h2>Determine your study goals</h2>\nCreate goals at the beginning of each week. For example: what you plan to accomplish and why? Once you have decided on your study goals, you will need to transfer your goals into your study plan. For example what you will be working on when studying.\n<h2>Stick to your schedule</h2>\nAlthough having no strict deadlines is one of the numerous benefits of home learning, you should still stick to your schedule. Even if it is just a rough estimate of when you want to finish your assignments. You will feel a lot better by spreading yourwork load out throughout the duration of your course. Therefore you will not be rushing to finish it at the end.\n<h2>Balance your schedule</h2>\nBy achieving a balanced schedule and making time for other activities, you will be more refreshed and devoted to studying when you come back to it. Make sure you give yourself some breaks or you will get discouraged and will be tempted to give up.\n\n<h2>When you make a study plan - you\'ll give yourself a better chance of success</h2>\n\nIncreasing numbers of students are attracted to distance learning but unless you have the discipline to keep working through your course it\'s unlikely you\'ll achieve what you want to achieve.  When you make a study plan, you\'re making a statement of intent. Make the plan and stick to it if you want to succeed.',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-02-26 11:58:44','2017-03-09 12:40:52',2,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=4367',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(99,'How to make a study plan','4367-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'<strong>What is a study plan?</strong>\n\nIt is an organised schedule that you can use to determine study times, learning objectives and goals. With a study plan you can dedicate certain days and times for studying around all of your other commitments. When studying in distance learning, a study plan is advised. This is due to the fact that you will not have constant reminders off an instructor. Therefore you will need to have your own determination and self-discipline, to achieve success.\n\n<strong>Create a table with your current activities</strong>\n\nMake a one week time table and note:\n<ul>\n	<li>The daily activities you partake in</li>\n	<li>When you are at work/school</li>\n	<li>When you are at home and with family</li>\n	<li>When you eat and sleep</li>\n</ul>\nOnce you have done this, look for times you can dedicate your time to studying. These days and times may be consistent throughout every week.\n\n<strong>Develop a schedule </strong>\n\nFrom your current timetable, make a mark in your planner and calendar of all the available days and times devoted to studying. Make sure you block out your studying times on your calendar. You should do this by making it visible and bold, so you don?t forget it. By making it bold will suggest that it is important and you shouldn?t miss studying. You should also add the subject you are studying, in case you have more than one course to study. This will help you devote enough time to each.\n\n<strong>Determine your study goals</strong>\n\nCreate goals at the beginning of each week. For example what you plan to accomplish and why. Once you have decided on your study goals, you will need to transfer your goals into your study plan. For example what you will be working on when studying.\n\n<strong>Stick to your schedule</strong>\n\nIf you do not stick to your study plan, you will fall behind. This may mean that work will be rushed and goals will not be met. It is important to stick to your schedule and will work best when it is followed on a consistent basis.\n\n<strong>Balance your schedule</strong>\n\nBy achieving a balanced schedule and making time for other activities, you will be more refreshed and devoted to studying when you come back to it. Make sure you give yourself some breaks or you will get discouraged and will be tempted to give up.',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-04 11:33:24','2016-01-04 11:33:24',1,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/2016/01/04/4367-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(100,'How to find your talent','how-to-find-your-talent',NULL,NULL,'Are you struggling to find your talent? Don\'t think you actually have one? Everybody is good at something so take note of these tips on how tofind your talent:\n<h2>Listen to others</h2>\nThose around you often know what your talents are. They will tell you that you are good at something, but you probably never listen to them. This is the time to listen.\n<h2>What do you find easy?</h2>\nThe things that you find easy may not be easy for other people. They may struggle whilst you feel as though it is a ?walk in the park?.\n<h2>What do you enjoy?</h2>\nIf you are drawn to something then it is classed as a natural talent. These may be things that you love to do, especially in your free time. For example: Are there any sports you love to take part in? Or any shows you like to watch?\n<h2>Shut up already</h2>\nIf there?s a specific subject you keep going on about and love to talk about, then this may be one of your hidden talents.\n<h2>Honest Assessment</h2>\nAsk people you know what you?re most talented at without bringing up any of your bad habits. You should aim to ask people individually, as no one can interfere and you will get a more accurate assessments. When you have put together your findings, you will be able to figure out your hidden talents.\n\nNow you know how to find your talent go and use it!',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-18 13:10:27','2017-03-29 13:06:54',2,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=4370',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
