	(108,'How to build on your talents','',NULL,NULL,'Now you have found your talent, you need to build on them. This will make you get better in what you are good at. Here are a few ways in which you can do this:\n\n<strong>Don?t compare yourself with others</strong>\n\nDo not compare yourself to others. If you are charged by someone else?s talent, but do not give permission to explore those sides of yourself, then you should consider working with these people. You will then be able to learn from one another and gain new skills.\n\n<strong>Concentrate on strengths </strong>\n\nThe things that you find easy may not be easy for other people. They may struggle whilst you feel as though it is a ?walk in the park?. Assess what your strengths are and forget your weaknesses. Put them aside, as it will only bring you misery and make you doubt yourself. Concentrating on strengths helps give you a sense of success and fulfilment.\n\n<strong>Work with someone</strong>\n\nIf you work with someone you will go far together, as you will both believe in each other. You will both have each other?s backs, so you can both help and put your skills together to get the best possible result. For example: Albert Einstein leaned on his wife to help and support him through his work.\n\n<strong>Failure is motivation</strong>\n\nEverybody makes mistakes and things don?t always go our way. By failing you can reset, revise and reassess to make you improve yourself. For example Steve Jobs was fired from the company he founded, however her came back to save it from extinction.',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-03-29 12:03:30','2017-03-29 12:03:30',1,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=4383',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
