	(118,'How to manage stress','4393-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'<strong>A varied and healthy diet</strong>\n\nIt is very important that you eat lots of fresh foods. Rather than ordering a pizza or getting fast food, cooking from scratch will allow you to include those fresh ingredients. This will make you become healthier and cause stress levels to decrease. Also juices such as orange and grapefruit are good for reducing stress and for your immune system too.\n\n<strong>Listen to music</strong>\n\nPutting on some music while you study can help you stay calm and relaxed. It will put you in a better frame of mind and make studying less of a chore.\n\n<strong>Exercise</strong>\n\nOne of the best ways to reduce stress is to exercise. Doing some kind of sport helps your body produce endorphins, which make you feel good. Joining a sports club will also help with stress, especially with regular contact with other people. Even going out for a walk for 30 minutes can help decrease stress levels.\n\n<strong>Meditation</strong>\n\nYou may discard this tip or think it?s not for you, but sitting quietly for 10 minutes can really help with stress. Good breathing techniques allow more oxygen to flow through your bloodstream. This helps you keep calm, relaxed and stress free. Give it a go!\n\n<strong>Take regular breaks</strong>\n\nShort breaks are good for relaxing, but you need to remember longer breaks are important too. Maybe take a weekend off to reward yourself for all of the studying throughout the week. Make sure you include these breaks in your studying. You will then come back to your work feeling refreshed and ready to start again.\n\n<strong>Get a pet</strong>\n\nAmazingly, studies show that spending time with animals is good for our health. Our bodies release hormones that make us feels happy and can lower the amount of stress in our systems. If you haven?t got a pet visit a family or friend that has.\n\n<strong>Sleep</strong>\n\nThe majority of people find that productivity increases when they have 20 minute naps. Make sure you don?t spend all of your time on social media sites and using your electronic devices. This will leave your even more stressed.\n\n<strong>Quit Smoking </strong>\n\nResearch on smoking reveals that nicotine suppresses the hormone serotonin, which fights stress.\n\n<strong>Look at the positive side</strong>\n\nIf you have made a mistake on the last assignment you sent off or you have missed a deadline. It?s not the end of the world. See it as a positive on how you can improve your skills. You now know you need to plan ahead and read your work thoroughly.\n\n<strong>Laugh</strong>\n\nLaughing causes an increase of oxygen and blood flow, which lowers stress levels. So if you?re stressed, laugh a bit more!',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-04 12:19:16','2016-01-04 12:19:16',1,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/2016/01/04/4393-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(119,'How to speed read','how-to-speed-read',NULL,NULL,'Do you wish you could read fast and understand the information at the same time? Then you can do this by teaching yourself how to speed read, which will help when you are studying. Here are a few tips on how to speed read:\n<h2>Stop talking to yourself</h2>\nThe majority of readers move their throats as if they were speaking the words. By doing this it slows down the speed you can read information. To prevent this from happening, you should chew gum or hum whilst reading.\n<h2>Hide words you?ve already read</h2>\nWhen reading you should cover the text that you have already read, as your eyes often move back to earlier words. This does not improve any understanding. If your eyes jump back to several lines behind, that is a sign you need to slow down.\n<h2>Understand eye movements</h2>\nIt has been proven that we can only read when our eyes have stopped moving. Your eyes move jerkily, skipping and stopping on random words. You should improve this line by line (although this may be difficult at first!). Studies show that you can read eight letters to the right of your eye position and four to the left. This works out to two or three words at a time.\n<h2>Make fewer eye movements</h2>\nYour brain decides where to move your eyes. It looks at how long or familiar the following words look. If you train your eyes to move to specific places on the page, it will allow you to read faster.\n<h2>Set a pace faster than you can understand</h2>\nIn order to become fast at reading and being able to understand the information, you need to set your pace faster than you would normally read. By doing this it will allow you to understand the main points quicker. Why not practice with this small exercise:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Whilst reading a piece of text, in your head say ?one one thousand? calmly. You should aim to finish the quote at the same time as finishing a line from the piece of text. Even if you don?t understand anything to begin with, this will help speed up your eye movement. You should keep repeating this whilst getting faster.</li>\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-02-24 13:17:44','2017-03-29 13:48:53',2,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=4395',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(120,'How to speed read','4395-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Wish you could read fast and understand the information at the same time? Then you should improve your speed reading skills. This will save time whilst studying. Here are a few tips on doing just that:\n\n<strong>Stop talking to yourself</strong>\n\nThe majority of readers move their throats as if they were speaking the words. By doing this it slows down the speed you can read information. To prevent this from happening, you should chew gum or hum whilst reading.\n\n<strong>Hide words you?ve already read</strong>\n\nWhen reading you should cover the text that you have already read, as your eyes often move back to earlier words. These do not improve any understanding. If your eyes jump back to several lines behind, that is a sign you need to slow down.\n\n<strong>Understand eye movements</strong>\n\nYou can only read when your eyes have stopped. Your eyes move jerkily, skipping and stopping on random words. You should improve this line by line, although it may be difficult. Studies show that you can read eight letters to the right of your eye position and four to the left. This works out to two or three words a t a time.\n\n<strong>Make fewer eye movements</strong>\n\nYour brain decides where to move your eyes. It looks at how long or familiar the following words look. If you train your eyes to move to specific places on the page, it will allow you to read faster.\n\n<strong>Set a pace faster than you can understand</strong>\n\nIn order to become fast at reading and being able to understand the information, you need to set your pace faster than you would normally read. By doing this it will allow you to understand the main points, without being time-consuming. Why not practice with this small exercise:\n<ul>\n	<li>Whilst reading a piece of text, in your head say ?one one thousand? calmly. You should aim to finish the quote at the same time as finishing a line from the piece of text. Even if you don?t understand anything to begin with, this will help speed up your eye movement. You should keep repeating this whilst getting faster.</li>\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-04 12:21:19','2016-01-04 12:21:19',1,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/2016/01/04/4395-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(121,'How 4 words cost a company half a billion pounds','how-4-words-cost-a-company-half-a-billion-pounds',NULL,NULL,'The Chief Executive of popular high street jewellery chain Ratner\'s damaged the brand so much that he was fired and the company had to be renamed. And all because of 4 words that he uttered at a Directors dinner.\n\nGerald Ratner talked to the crowd about the low price products his company offered.\n\n<blockquote>\n\"People say: \'How can you sell this for such a low price?\'\nI say: \'because it\'s total crap\'\"</blockquote>\n\nThe share price plunged. Nearly 300 stores closed between 1992 and 1994. Nobody wants to buy products that even the manufacturer denounces as \'crap.\' This gaffe is now so legendary that the expression \'doing a Ratner\' is used to indicate an attitude of contempt towards the consumer.\n\nThe most important Public Relations lesson here is that the man at the top should be a brand evangelist and remember what the legendary advertising man David Ogilvy once said: \"The consumer is not a moron, she is your wife.\"\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/public-relations-3.html\">Learn more about Public Relations on our Level 3 course &raquo; </a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-06 09:22:25','2016-01-06 09:22:25',2,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=4402',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
