	(124,'A report about the benefits of killing your customers? That\'s PR suicide!','pr-suicide',NULL,NULL,'Cigarettes can make people very ill.  After decades where cigarette companies denied the link between smoking and lung cancer, Tobacco giant Philip Morris decided on a different approach. It was bold. And it was also completely stupid.\n\nClaiming that the government will save $24 million in healthcare, pension and public housing costs because your product could kill people is (to put it mildly) not the smartest Public Relations move. But that\'s precisely what they did.\n\nIn 2000, they commissioned a study to investigate the impact of smoking on the public finances in the Czech Republic. The report concluded that the tax revenue and levels of early mortality outweighed the costs of healthcare.\n\nThis is one idea that should have gone up in smoke.\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/public-relations-3.html\" class=\"blog-cta\">Interested in PR? Study our Public Relations course </a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-07 12:17:17','2017-03-06 14:53:11',2,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=4409',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(125,'Philip committed PR suicide with their study into the benefits of smoking-related deaths','breaking-the-habit-2',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-04 13:12:34','2017-03-06 14:54:13',1,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/iStock_000003299023_Large.jpg',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(126,'Are there any benefits to killing your own customers?','4409-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Claiming that the government will save $24 million in healthcare, pension and public housing costs because a product that you buy will probably kill you is (to put it mildly) not the smartest Public Relations move. But that\'s precisely what Philip Morris did.\n\nTobacco giant Philip Morris scored a sensational PR own goal when they claimed that one of the benefits of smoking was that it killed sick people.\n\nThe study commissioned in 2000, investigated the impact of smoking on the public finances in the Czech Republic. The results suggested that the tax revenue and levels of early mortality outweighed the costs of healthcare.\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/public-relations-3.html\">Learn more about Public Relations on our Level 3 course </a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-04 13:13:41','2016-01-04 13:13:41',1,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/2016/01/04/4409-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
