	(139,'3 reasons to study public relations with us','3-reasons-study-public-relations',NULL,NULL,'Do you want to know how to create Public Relations campaigns that get great results?\n\nIf you\'re a marketer and want to improve your job prospects, adding PR skills to your CV is a great way to boost your earning potential.\n\nHere are 3 reasons why you should study public relations with us\n\n<h2>1. Find out how to run a PR campaign</h2>\n\nBusinesses want to get their marketing message seen by their target audience and to project a good corporate image. This is where an effective and carefully planned Public Relations campaign comes in.\n\nAn effective campaign needs to have:\n\n<ul>\n<li>a clearly defined set of goals,</li>\n<li>an understanding of who you are targeting,</li>\n<li>a carefully considered strategy</li>\n</ul>\n\n...which is why our first module shows you exactly how to do this.\n\n<h2>2. Learn how to handle a crisis</h2>\n\n24 hour news and social media highlight corporate mistakes very quickly. All of a sudden a small customer service problem can go viral and damage the reputation of a company.\n\nWe can show you how to deal with problems that would otherwise cause serious damage to a brand.\n\n<h2>3. Improve your internal PR skills</h2>\n\nPlenty of organisations claim that their employees are their greatest asset, yet one of the biggest concerns of many employees is a lack of internal communication.\n\nNot all managers are good communicators and many don\'t recognise its importance. In our dedicated course unit, you\'ll learn how managers can communicate effectively both in terms of the messages and the media they can use.\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/public-relations-3.html\" class=\"blog-cta\">Study Public Relations with our Level 3 course</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-04 14:54:50','2017-03-06 12:39:02',2,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=4437',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(140,'3 reasons to start studying public relations with us','4437-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Do you want to know how to create PR campaigns that get good results?\n\nIf you\'re a marketer and want to improve your job prospects, adding PR skills to your CV is a great way to boost your earning potential.\n\nHere are 3 reasons why you should boost your skills by completing our Public Relations Level 3 course:\n\n<h2>1. Find out how to run a PR campaign</h2>\n\nBusinesses want to get their marketing message seen by their target audience and to project a good corporate image. This is where an effective and carefully planned Public Relations campaign comes in.\n\nAn effective campaign needs to have:\n\n<ul>\n<li>a clearly defined set of goals,</li>\n<li>an understanding of who you are targeting,</li>\n<li>a carefully considered strategy</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n...which is why our first module shows you exactly how to do this.\n\n<h2>2. Learn how to handle a crisis</h2>\n\n24 hour news and social media highlight corporate mistakes very quickly. All of a sudden a small customer service problem can go viral and damage the reputation of a company.\n\nWe can show you how to deal with problems that would otherwise cause serious damage to a brand.\n\n<h2>3. Improve your internal PR skills</h2>\n\nPlenty of organisations claim that their employees are their greatest asset, yet one of the biggest concerns of many employees is a lack of internal communication.\n\nNot all managers are good communicators and many don\'t recognise the importance of good communication. In our dedicated course unit, you\'ll learn how managers can communicate effectively both in terms of the messages and the media they can use.\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/public-relations-3.html\">Learn more about Public Relations on our Level 3 course &raquo; </a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-04 14:54:47','2016-01-04 14:54:47',1,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/2016/01/04/4437-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(141,'5 Memory techniques to help your studying','5-memory-techniques',NULL,NULL,'When you are studying do you sometimes get that feeling that nothing?s going in and you can?t remember anything that you?ve looked at? Here are 5 memory techniques to help your studying...\n<h2>Give it a meaning</h2>\nYou should try to assign meaningfulness to things. This can be done by applying knowledge to something important to you. For example: something you saw in a documentary or an everyday experience.\n<h2>Keep going over information</h2>\nKeep saying the information over and over again (speaking out loud is best). You should do this until you don?t need your notes in front of you. The more times you go over it the less likely you are to forget it. You should keep going back to what you have learnt throughout the day/week to see if you can still remember it.\n<h2>Teach someone else</h2>\nA great way that you can memorisesomething is by teaching someone else. This will determine whether you have understood and learnt the information. If no one wants to listen to you, you can always teach the wall, just make sure no ones looking first!\n<h2>Use memory devices</h2>\nThere are many different devices to help with memorising. These include: mapping information, post it notes and note making. The best technique is using flash cards. These will help you break down information into smaller and easier chunks. This will be simpler to memorise and will be a quick memory buzz for you.\n<h2>Rhyming and story telling</h2>\nPutting information into a rhyme or story is another way of making it easier to remember. For example my very easy method just speeds up naming planets. This represents the order and names of planets: Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, Neptune, Pluto.\n\nTaking these 5 memory techniques on board will help you defeat forgetfulness and get you on track to successful studying!',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-22 12:36:46','2017-03-29 13:12:54',2,'http://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=4440',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
