	(204,'Increase your knowledge of the Youth Justice Service with our new course','4585-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Are you interested in learning about the youth justice system in England and Wales? Do you want to understand how the legal framework works with children?s needs and rights? Then with our new Youth Justice Service course, you can learn just that, from home!\n\nThe youth justice system helps protect offenders and promotes their well-being. First-time entrants, re-offenders and young people in custody all are very important and need to be reduced. The number of people re-offending has increased, which means the youth justice system need to help those not to commit again.\n<blockquote>?Lisa took part in gang activity. She used her time in custody positively and took part in education. This enabled her to secure employment upon release. Her relationship with prison staff and positive attitude led her to be deemed suitable for release on temporary licence (ROTL) that helped secure her qualifications and employment?</blockquote>\nMaking sure young people do not re-offend is one of the main duties of the youth justice service. Not only is this positive news for the community it is also rewarding to know you have helped a young person get their life on track. So learn how to do this on our Youth Justice Service.\n\nTake a look at our Youth Justice Services Level 3 course&gt;&gt;',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-15 15:21:42','2016-01-15 15:21:42',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/2016/01/15/4585-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
