	(209,'3 reasons to study public relations with us','4437-autosave-v1',NULL,NULL,'Do you want to know how to create Public Relations campaigns that get great results?\n\nIf you\'re a marketer and want to improve your job prospects, adding PR skills to your CV is a great way to boost your earning potential.\n\nHere are 3 reasons why you should study public relations with us\n\n<h2>1. Find out how to run a PR campaign</h2>\n\nBusinesses want to get their marketing message seen by their target audience and to project a good corporate image. This is where an effective and carefully planned Public Relations campaign comes in.\n\nAn effective campaign needs to have:\n\n<ul>\n<li>a clearly defined set of goals,</li>\n<li>an understanding of who you are targeting,</li>\n<li>a carefully considered strategy</li>\n</ul>\n\n...which is why our first module shows you exactly how to do this.\n\n<h2>2. Learn how to handle a crisis</h2>\n\n24 hour news and social media highlight corporate mistakes very quickly. All of a sudden a small customer service problem can go viral and damage the reputation of a company.\n\nWe can show you how to deal with problems that would otherwise cause serious damage to a brand.\n\n<h2>3. Improve your internal PR skills</h2>\n\nPlenty of organisations claim that their employees are their greatest asset, yet one of the biggest concerns of many employees is a lack of internal communication.\n\nNot all managers are good communicators and many don\'t recognise its importance. In our dedicated course unit, you\'ll learn how managers can communicate effectively both in terms of the messages and the media they can use.\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/public-relations-3.html\" class=\"blog-cta\">Study Public Relations with our Level 3 course</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-03-06 12:37:54','2017-03-06 12:37:54',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/2016/01/20/4437-autosave-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(210,'3 reasons you should offer payroll management','3-reasons-to-study-payroll-course',NULL,NULL,'Do you work as a freelance bookkeeper? Studying our ICB Payroll course could be a great way to boost your earning capacity. Here are 3 reasons why you should offer a payroll management service:\n\n<h2>Outsourcing on the rise - why not profit from it?</h2>\n<p>Startups have been an important part of Britain\'s economic recovery. In 2014, 581,000 new companies were formed- an all time high! Growing companies will want to outsource more specialised tasks. Take advantage of it!</p>\n<h2>Be a convenient one stop shop for bookkeeping and payroll</h2>\n<p>Businesses want to keep the number of separate companies they have to deal with to a minimum. So if you\'re offering bookkeeping and payroll services, you\'re keeping things simple for small businesses who want to sell their products, not be bogged down with accounts.</p>\n<h2>Boost the amount you earn per client</h2>\n<p>If you want to grow your bookkeeping business then you\'ve got two ways to do it. Get more clients or increase the value you\'re getting from each one. By providing payroll management you can earn more from your existing clients and you\'re more likely to keep them.</p>\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/icb-payroll-level-3.html\" class=\"blog-cta\">Study our ICB payroll course from home</a>\n\n<h2>Why study a payroll course with Open Study College</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Winner! ICB Luca Awards - Tutor of the Year 2014</li>\n<li>Winner! ICB Luca Awards - Small Accredited Training Provider of the Year 2014</li>\n<li>Course accredited by the world\'s largest bookkeeping organisation</li>\n<li>Over 50,000 people have improved their skills with us</li>\n<li>Study from home, at your own pace</li>\n<li>Full support from your tutor</li>\n<li>Easy to understand course materials</li>\n<li>FREE NUS Extra Card - Exclusive discounts at high street shops</li>\n<li>FREE CV writing service - Get a better CV to apply for better jobs</li>\n</ul>\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/icb-payroll-level-3.html\" class=\"blog-cta\" >Enrol on our ICB payroll course</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-20 14:53:16','2017-03-22 09:46:28',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=4611',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(211,'3 reasons you should offer payroll management','4611-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Do you work as a freelance bookkeeper?\n\nHere are 3 reasons why you should start offering payroll management as well:\n\n<ol>\n<li>1. Outsourcing set to rise\n<p>\nThe rise of startup companies has been an interesting aspect of Britain\'s gradual economic recovery. In 2011, 396,000 new companies were formed- the highest figure since 2007. As these companies grow and hire extra staff, small companies which might previously have handled as much work internally as possible will start to outsource some of the more specialised tasks. </p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n2. Be a one stop shop for bookkeeping and payroll\nA lot of businesses will want to keep the number of separate outside companies they have to deal with to a minimum. So if you\'re offering bookkeeping and payroll services, you\'re keeping things nice and straightforward for small businesses who want to spend time developing and selling their own products, not busy with accounts and finance.\n\n3. Increase the amount you earn per client\nIf you want to grow your bookkeeping business then you\'ve got two ways to do it. Get more clients or increase the value you\'re getting from each one. By providing payroll management you can earn more from your existing clients and you\'re more likely to keep them.\n\nOpen Study College offer the ICB Payroll Management Level 3 Diploma as well as a range of individual bookkeeping courses and the ICB Bookkeeping Complete package. All courses are studied from home, at your own pace with full tutor support. To find out more call Open Study College on 0800 970 9131 or visit the website\n',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-01-20 14:18:17','2016-01-20 14:18:17',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/2016/01/20/4611-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
