	(281,'Gain an sight into PTSD from home!','gain-an-sight-into-ptsd-from-home',NULL,NULL,'PTSD (Post Traumatic Stress Disorder) is a mental health condition that is triggered by a terrifying event. This can be in the form or witnessing or experiencing it. Individuals with PTSD can be prone to flashbacks, nightmares and severe anxiety, as well as uncontrollable thoughts about the event. Those people that have this terrible disorder may feel stressed or frightened even when they are not in danger. The majority of people that suffer from PTSD include: military troops who served in wars, rescue workers, survivors of accidents, rape, physical or sexual abuse, and other crimes.\n\nPTSD among military personnel has risen 26 percent over since 2014-2015 and this is still rising.\n<blockquote>?You have to learn you?re never going to get rid of it; you have to learn how to live with it?. ?Brown</blockquote>\nBrown was a military policeman stationed in Saudi Arabia during Operation Desert Storm. His duties included sifting through the remains of car accidents and bombings. Many of the corpses he saw were unrecognisable as human bodies. Browns terrible and unimaginable experiences left him with flashbacks, which lead to PTSD.\n\nDo want to learn more about this disorder? Then enrol on our PTSD Course today!\n\nTake a look at our Post Traumatic Stress Disorder Level 3 Course &gt;&gt;',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-03-21 13:16:43','2016-03-21 13:16:43',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=4945',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
