	(288,'Explore Feng Shui from home!','explore-feng-shui-from-home',NULL,NULL,'Feng Shui is a Chinese ancient art and science which was developed 3,000 years ago. It is a complex body of knowledge that reveals how to balance the energies of any given space to assure health and good fortune for people inhabiting it. Feng means wind and Shui means water. Wind and water in the Chinese culture are associated with good health. From this, good Feng Shui has come to mean good fortune, whilst bad luck and misfortune is represented by bad Feng Shui. Many people use Feng Shui to help decorate their homes. There are 5 main elements of Feng Shui, these include:\n<h2>Wood</h2>\nWood is the energy of expansion, unlimited growth, abundance, vision, steadiness and survival. It is associated with the colours green and brown and is connected to upward growth, being joyful, happy and grounded at the same time. When a healthy plant or tree has deep roots it can stand tall, reaching out to the sky and sun. This reinforces the balance between grounding and giving an uplifting energy.\n<h2>Fire</h2>\nFire is the energy of the bright sun, happy celebrations, glorious and joyful achievements. It also brings the energy of strong sexual desires, passions and romance. The main colours associated with the fire element are: red, yellow and orange. There is no good Feng Shui without the bright, bold and happy energy of the fire element. Using too little of the fire element in your house will limit the happy energy, too much will increase conflicts and rising tempers.\n<h2>Earth</h2>\nEarth is the energy of nourishment, stability, support and caring patience. It is associated with the colours beige, sandy and taupe and brings a welcome warm feeling. The earth element is represented by sustaining life, protecting, cherishing and healing.\n<h2>Metal</h2>\nMetal is the energy of purity, preciseness, freshness, discipline and clarity. It is associated with the colour white and grey. Using the metal element is good when you are frustrated, overwhelmed, have a lack of direction or just experience low, lazy energy.\n\nDo you want to know more about Feng Shui? Then enrol on our course today!\n\nTake a look at our Feng Shui Level 2 Course&gt;&gt;',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-03-22 10:38:50','2016-03-22 10:38:50',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=4956',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
