	(400,'How to stay organised whilst studying','how-to-stay-organised-whilst-studying',NULL,NULL,'Getting yourself organised before studying is an important first step, which many people skip. In order to stay organised whilst studying you need to take note of these 3 important P?s: place, planning and prioritise:\n<h2>Place</h2>\nScientists have revealed that a messy environment restricts your ability to focus and limits your brain\'s capability to process information. Clutter also creates distraction, which is why you should aim to use the first 5 minutes before studying to clean your environment and to gather the materials you need for your learning. This will help prepare you for studying.\n<h2>Planning</h2>\nAs distance learning allows you to be flexible and has no strict deadlines, you may want to consider targets. To help with this write down in a planner or on a calendar when you wish to complete your assignments. You will then know how long to spend on each one and it will enableyou to measure your progress.\n<h2>Prioritise</h2>\nDon?t spend hours on a task that doesn\'t need to be completed any time soon. Start by more important tasks that have deadlines approaching. By prioritising your work, it will allow you to get the assignments that have shorter deadlines completed first. This will prevent you from falling behind and rushing your work at the end of your course.',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-06-28 09:59:35','2016-06-28 09:59:35',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=5384',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(401,'How to stay organised whilst studying: The 3 P?s','5384-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'In order to stay organised whilst studying you need to take note of these 3 important P?s: place, planning and prioritise. This will help you on your way to achieving. Take a look at the 3 P?s now:\n<h2>Place</h2>\nStudy somewhere quiet such as in a library or a room in your house. Make sure there are few interruptions when you study. Avoid places where you are likely to run into your friends. Stay concentrated and determined to learn everything you can.\n<h2>Planning</h2>\nAs distance learning allows you to be flexible and has no strict deadlines, you may want to consider targets. To help with this write down in a planner or on a calendar when you wish to complete your assignments. You will then know how long to spend on each one and it will allow you measure your progress. Make sure you organise your work and your place of study, so you do not have any distractions whilst learning.\n<h2>Prioritise</h2>\nMake sure you prioritise your work. Don?t spend hours on a task that doesn\'t need to be completed any time soon. Start by more important tasks that have deadlines approaching. By prioritising your work it will allow you to get the assignments that have shorter deadlines completed first. This will prevent you from falling behind and rushing your work at the end of your course.',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-05-19 15:35:39','2016-05-19 15:35:39',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/2016/05/19/5384-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(402,'3 business mistakes you can?t afford to make','3-business-mistakes-you-cant-afford-to-make',NULL,NULL,'Are you thinking about setting up your own business? Then you need to take a look at these 3 mistakes you can?t afford to make:\n<h2>Poor cash flow management</h2>\nOne of the main reasons why businesses fail is due to poor cash flow management. Many companies forget that they need enough cash coming into the business in order to meet their necessary expenditure on a monthly basis. Ignoring this will ultimately lead to business failure.\n<h2>No focus</h2>\nIt is particularly common when a project expands out of control more than you anticipated. In many cases organisations enter markets that they know nothing about and forget to focus on successfully managing their core business. Companies that concentrate on a small number of customers take a huge risk. If a small number of people make up the bulk of the turnover, then organisations should look for new work.\n<h2>Lack of insurance</h2>\nBusiness insurance is a definite requirement for all organisations. However many companies are uninsured, which means they run the risk of falling into expensive compensation claims or heavy bills in the event of problems. Businesses should invest in the correct insurance in order to protect themselves.\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/business_courses.html\">Take a look at our business courses &gt;&gt;</a>\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/business_courses.html\">Enrol on a business course today!</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-06-30 11:22:54','2016-06-30 11:22:54',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=5387',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(403,'3 business mistakes you can?t afford to make','5387-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Are you thinking of setting up your own business? Maybe you already have? Then you need to take a look at these 3 mistakes you can?t afford to make:\n<h2>Poor cash flow management</h2>\nOne of the main reasons why businesses fail is due to poor cash flow management. Many companies forget that they need enough cash coming into the business in order to meet their necessary expenditure on a monthly basis. Ignoring this will ultimately lead to business failure.\n<h2>No focus</h2>\nHaving a lack of focus on your business is another common mistake. This can also be defined as ?scope creep?. It is particularly common when a project expands out of control more than you anticipated. In many cases organisations enter markets that they know nothing about and forget to focus on successfully managing their core business. In addition companies that concentrate on a small number of customers take a huge risk. If a small number of people make up the bulk of the turnover, then organisations should look for new work.\n<h2>Lack of insurance</h2>\nBusiness insurance is a definite requirement for all organisations. However many companies are uninsured, which means they run the risk of falling into expensive compensation claims or heavy bills in the event of problems. Businesses should invest in the correct insurance in order to protect themselves.\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/business_courses.html\">Take a look at our business courses &gt;&gt;</a>\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/business_courses.html\">Enrol on a business course today!</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-05-20 11:03:51','2016-05-20 11:03:51',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/2016/05/20/5387-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(404,'How the growth of Starbucks destroyed their brand identity','how-the-growth-of-starbucks-destroyed-their-brand-identity',NULL,NULL,'Brand identity is a vital part of a business and can either lead to the success or failure of a company. Which is what lead to a brand identity hiccup for Starbucks!\n\nTrying to increase their sales they focused on trying to add value to their business by offering free Wi-Fi and . They also improved the quality and standards of their beverages.\n\nNot making much progress, Starbucks looked closely into this and realised they were expanding too much, which was ultimately destroying their brand image. Their premium priced coffee was no longer special and didn\'t have the ?soul? of a neighbourhood store like it did before.\n\nStarbucks were then placed with two tough decisions: cutting their price and losing their ?premium? and ?exclusive? brand identity or to cut distribution. Knowing the importance of their branding, Starbucks finally made the decision to close 600 stores. Sometimes less is more in the world of marketing and therefore they should have focused on improving their original sales.\n\nAs it is challenging to trade as a public company whilst having a premium-priced brand, Starbucks have realised they need to grow at a more controlled pace.\n\nLearn more about brand identity in our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/introduction-marketing-3.html?dc=4\">introduction to marketing course!</a>\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/introduction-marketing-3.html?dc=4\">Take a look at our Level 3 Introduction to Marketing course &gt;&gt;</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-06-09 11:08:48','2016-06-09 11:08:48',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=5390',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(405,'How the growth of Starbucks destroyed their brand identity','5390-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Brand identity is a vital part of a business and can either lead to the success or failure of a company ? which is what Starbucks ignored.\n\nThey focused on trying to add value to their business by offering free Wi-Fi and creating and selling its own music. They also improved the quality and standards of their beverages.\n\nNot making much progress, Starbucks looked closely into this and realised they were expanding too much, which was ultimately destroying their brand image. Their premium priced coffee was no longer special and didn\'t have the ?soul? of a neighbourhood store like it did before.\n\nStarbucks were then placed with two tough decisions: cutting their price and losing their ?premium? and ?exclusive? brand identity or to cut distribution. Knowing the importance of their branding, Starbucks finally made the decision to close 600 stores. Sometimes less is more in the world of marketing and therefore they should have focused on improving their original sales.\n\nAs it is challenging to trade as a public company whilst having a premium-priced brand, Starbucks have realised they need to grow at a more controlled pace.\n\nLearn more about brand identity in our introduction to marketing course!\n\nTake a look at our Level 3 Introduction to Marketing course &gt;&gt;',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-05-20 12:44:01','2016-05-20 12:44:01',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/2016/05/20/5390-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(406,'Top 5 Interview Mistakes','top-5-interview-mistakes',NULL,NULL,'Have you got an interview lined up? Then you will need to avoid these top 5 interview mistakes:\n<h2>Lack of preparation</h2>\nOne of the most vital mistakes that nearly everyone makes is not preparing for their job interview. You should try to predict some of the tough questions that may come up and gather some answers together. Before the big day you should also research the company, this will show you are interested in working with them.\n<h2>Not matching communication styles</h2>\nMany people make the mistake of not effectively communicating to their interviewer. You should let them set the tone in order to make you both feel at ease and allow the conversation to flow naturally. A technique that you should use is mirroring. This is the best way for you to bond and connect with your interviewer.\n<h2>Talking too much</h2>\nInterviewers switch off from people that talk too much and believe they cannot get to the point.You should talk for just enough time for you to get yourpoint across with including relevant information.Interviewers also find that people who are nervous are prone to be talkative. So practice answering questions that you might be asked in advanced and avoid being too talkative.\n<h2>Negative comments</h2>\nSaying negative things about your last employer will be viewed as disrespect. Even if you have a lot of reasonable complaints from you previous work, you should try and put a positive spin on your experiences.\n<h2>Giving information on salary and earnings</h2>\nBy speaking freely about your current income could weaken your earning potential. The wage offered to you could be a lot more that your current wage, however by giving them this information could mean they decrease their offer.\n\nAvoiding these 5 simple mistakes could be the difference between you and your perfect job!\n\nSo go and successfully defeat that dreaded interview!',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-07-01 12:49:56','2016-07-01 12:49:56',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=5393',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(407,'Top 5 Interview Mistakes','5393-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Have you got an interview lined up? Then you will need to avoid these top 5 interview mistakes:\n<h2>Lack of preparation</h2>\nOne of the most vital mistakes that nearly everyone makes is not preparing for their job interview. You should try to predict some of the tough questions that may come up and gather some answers together so you know what you?re going to say. Before the big day you should also research the company that you are having the interview with to display your interest in them.\n<h2>Not matching communication styles</h2>\nMany people make the mistake of not effectively communicating to their interviewer. You should let them set the tone in order to make you both feel at ease and allow the conversation to flow naturally. A technique that you should use is mirroring. This is the best way for you to bond and connect with your interviewer.\n<h2>Talking too much</h2>\nInterviewers switch off from people that talk too much. They believe that candidates that keep going on can?t get to the point. You should talk for just enough time for you to get to the point and give any additional and relevant information. Interviewers also find that people who are nervous are prone to be talkative. This comes across as being someone that is covering up something or outright lying. So practice answering questions that you might be asked in advanced and avoid being too talkative.\n<h2>Negative comments about your past employers or managers</h2>\nSaying negative things about your last employer will be viewed as disrespect. Even if you have a lot of reasonable complaints from you previous work, you should try and put a positive spin on your experiences.\n<h2>Giving information on salary and earnings</h2>\nBy speaking freely about your current income could weaken your earning potential. The wage offered to you could be a lot more that your current wage, however by giving them this information could mean they decrease their offer.\n\nAvoiding these 5 simple mistakes could be the difference between you getting the job and not getting the job.\n\nSo go and successfully defeat that dreaded interview for your dream job!',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-05-20 15:17:07','2016-05-20 15:17:07',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/2016/05/20/5393-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(408,'5 Top tips to help tackle your exams','5-exam-top-tips',NULL,NULL,'It?s that time of the year again ? exam season! We understand that this is a very stressful period for you, which is why you need to read these 5 top tips on how to tackle your exams:\n<h2>Are you stressing out?</h2>\nYou need to recognise if you?re stressing out and understandhow todeal with pressure. Trying to perform the best you can by cramming in any last bit of information can cause you to go into panic mode. Take a break and let your brain rest.Go for awalk and get some fresh air. This will help clear your mind before you go back to your revision.\n<h2>Avoid comparing abilities</h2>\nWe all despise of those people who brag about how much revision they have done or go on to tell us how they know everything. Try to ignore this and not compare yourself to them. Everybody has different revision approaches, so just make sure you use the method that suits you. Creating a realistic study timetable will help you plan your learning and keep you on track.\n<h2>Breathe</h2>\nIf you feel as though you are going into panic mode during the exam, sit back and breathe! Control it by taking deep breaths in and out the nose whilst counting to 5.\n<h2>Sleep</h2>\nYou should get a good night?s sleep the day before your exam. This will allow your brain to rest and help perform at its peak the following day. Research suggests that sleep plays an important role in memory, both before and after learning. Lack of adequate sleep affects mood, motivation, judgement, and your perception of events. So get your 8 hours sleep!\n<h2>Exercise and eat right</h2>\nPhysical activity works best at de-stressing the mind. Try fitting this in your revision timetable. Doing exercise will make you feel better about yourself and freshen up your mind. Alongside this make sure you eat right. Eating fruit and vegetables will fuel your brain and improve your performance ? so put down that chocolate bar!\n\nAlthough things are intense at the moment, just think about the feeling you will have once you walk out the exam hall!\n\nMake yourself proud and good luck, we know you can do it!',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-05-25 10:54:42','2017-05-02 13:55:02',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=5396',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
