	(426,'Top tips on how to impress an employer in an interview','5430',NULL,NULL,'Have you got an interview lined up? Maybe you?re having no luck in getting past the interview stage? Then take a look at these 5 top tips on how to impress an employer in an interview:\n<h2>Get there early</h2>\nTurning up early will show your interviewer that you are dedicated and the position means a lot to you. It will also show them that you appreciate the employer taking the time out to speak to you.You don?t want to be rushing around and panicking if you arrive late!\n<h2>Prepare</h2>\nPreparing for a job interview is vital if you want to impress. You should try to predict some of the tough questions that may come up and gather some answers together so you know what you?re going to say. Before the big day you should also research the company that you are having the interview with to display your interest in them. The more you know about the company the more able you will be to answer questions intelligently about it.\n<h2>Smile and dress professionally</h2>\nFirst impressions are very important, which is why you should amaze your interviewer straight away. Make sure you greet people with a firm handshake and always make eye contact when you are taking. In particular smile and look interested! You should also dress professionally as your appearance can say a lot about you as a person.\n<h2>Ask meaningful questions</h2>\nInterviewers like it when candidates ask questions about the job role they have applied for. So try to ask specific questions such as what the job entails or what the companies goals are. This will show them that you are interested in the job and the company.\n<h2>Say thank you</h2>\nThank the interviewer for taking time out to speak to you. You could even say thank you in an email, whilst, reiterating why you would be an asset to the company.\n\nA first impression is made in less than 30 seconds. Make sure those 30 seconds show you in the best possible light!',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-07-12 09:28:09','2016-07-12 09:28:09',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=5430',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
