	(526,'5 Reasons why you study zoology','5-reasons-why-you-study-zoology',NULL,NULL,'Do you love animals and want to know everything you can about them? Is your dream job to work with animals in the future? Then explore the natural world and take the first steps in becoming closer to achieving your amazing career as a zoologist! Here are 3 reasons why you should study our zoology course:\n<h2>Explore the evolution of species</h2>\nThis course will allow you to gain an insight into Darwin?s fascinating theory of evolution. It will enable you to understand how all species of organisms arise and develop through natural selection of small, inherited variations, which increase their ability to compete, survive, and reproduce.\n<h2>Gain an introduction into the living world</h2>\nFocus on the function and metabolic processes of the cell, historical development of cellular understanding and discover life?s origins both chemically and biologically. This great module will help you discover everything you need to know about the interesting life of organisms.\n<h2>Investigate complex vertebrates</h2>\nThis module has been designed so you can explore complex vertebrates including: fish, reptiles and amphibians, birds and mammals. After studying this unit you will be able to understand the requirements for a species to be classified as a bird, know about the biology of a fish and identify the difference between reptiles and amphibians.\n<h2>Discover how to maintain life in the animal kingdom</h2>\nYou will gain an insight into animal?s internal environment and explore their forms and functions in terms of the endocrine and nervous systems. This module will also help you discover how the digestive system uses mechanical and chemical methods to break down food into nutrient molecules that can be absorbed into the blood.\n<h2>Identify different skeletal systems in the natural world</h2>\nThe skeletal system is an animal?s internal support frame, so being able to recognise a variety of them is very important, especially if you want to work with animals in the future. You will be able to explore the different types of bones from facial to hyoid bones and understand how this structure helps animals move and protects their organs.\n\nBoost your skills and knowledge in zoology today with our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/zoology-level-3.html\">Level 3 course!</a>\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/zoology-level-3.html\">Take a look at our Zoology Level 3 course&gt;&gt;</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-07-18 09:57:42','2016-07-18 09:57:42',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=5741',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
