	(604,'5 vital skills of a personal assistant','5-vital-skills-of-a-personal-assistant',NULL,NULL,'Whether you want to work in a large or small business, the role of a personal assistant requires many skills to ensure the day-to-day running of the business goes smoothly. Here are 5 skills that are vital if you want to become a personal assistant:\n<h2>Communication</h2>\nOne of the main skills a personal assistant needs is excellent communication. A daily task of a PA will be to answer calls, handle enquires and complete various business documents, includingletters and emails. So making sure youare clear and give the correct information is very important.\n<h2>Organisation</h2>\nIt is the duty of a PA to manage the office, which is why you must be organised. Making sure files and information are up to date and colleagues have what they need to complete their work is your responsibility. Being organised will allow you to do yourjob a lot easier.\n<h2>Computer skills</h2>\nPersonal Assistantsneed to have excellent skills in presentation and word processing skills. As letter writing is a daily task of a PA, good Word processing skills are vital and are an essential role in the day-to-day running of an office.\n<h2>Planning skills</h2>\nAttending meetings isa regular occurrence in the working week for many personal assistants. It is their responsibility to plan these and make everyone aware about when and where they will be held. Excellent planning skills will also be needed in order for you to organise events.\n<h2>Recruiting skills</h2>\nRecruiting skills are needed to ensure the correct job vacancy details are displayed clearly, candidate information is looked after safely andcommunication with applicants is effective.\n\nSo if you want to become a Personal Assistant then boost your skills and knowledge with our<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/personal-assistant-3.html\">Level 3 course</a> today!\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/personal-assistant-3.html\">Take a look at our Personal Assistant Level 3 course&gt;&gt;</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-10-28 12:36:27','2017-03-16 09:24:57',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=5949',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(605,'5 vital skills a personal assistant needs','5949-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'The role of a personal assistant, whether in a large or small business, often requires that many skills are deployed for the benefit of the company, and that employees ensure that the day-to-day running of the business goes smoothly. Here are 5 vital skills a personal assistant needs to have:\n<h2>Excellent Communicator</h2>\nOne of the main skills a personal assistant needs is excellent communication. A daily task of a PA will be to answer calls, handle enquires and complete various business documents, from letters and emails. So making sure you are clear and giving the correct information is very important.\n<h2>Well organised</h2>\nIt is the duty of a PA to manage the office, which is why you must be organised. Making sure files and information are up to date and colleagues have what they need to complete their work is your responsibility. Being organised will allow you to find things and do your job easier.\n<h2>Out-standing computer skills</h2>\nYou will need to have good knowledge of spreadsheets, presentational and word processing skills. As a tool for letter writing, word processing software is one of the greatest inventions for those employed in this role. Spreadsheets also play an essential role in the day-to-day running of an office, and can help to streamline many of the routine tasks that are required to be undertaken by personal assistants.\n<h2>Exceptional planning skills</h2>\nFor the majority of personal assistants, attending meetings is a regular event in the working week. It is their responsibility to plan these and make everyone involved aware. It is also usual for a PA to take minutes when the meeting is being held. They will also have the task of arranging any events from the budgetary requirements to the health and safety issues.\n<h2>Good recruiting skills</h2>\nA personal assistant needs to ensure that the correct vacancy details are acquired, candidate information is looked after safely, that they communicate clearly with applicants after interviews and identify and discuss the process from interview to appointment.\n\nIf you want to learn about the skills of a<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/personal-assistant-3.html\"> personal assistant</a> then enrol on our Level 3 course today!\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/personal-assistant-3.html\">Take a look at our Personal Assistant Level 3 course&gt;&gt;</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-09-15 16:16:15','2016-09-15 16:16:15',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/2016/09/15/5949-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(606,'Introducing ? Ghost Hunting Level 2','introducing-ghost-hunting-level-2',NULL,NULL,'It?s Halloween, so why not celebrate by studying our Ghost Hunting Level 2 course. Do you have an unwanted presence in your house you want to get rid of? Maybe you want to arrange a ghost hunt, but don?t know how to? Or perhaps you want to know if you have a ghost living with you? Then our ghost hunting course is perfect for you! Here are 3 reasons why you should study our Level 2 course:\n<h2>Know when a ghost is present</h2>\nFrom strange noises, moved objects and sudden drops in temperature you will be able to learn when a ghost is present. Understand when a ghost is seeking attention and whether it has bad or good intentions.\n<h2>Preparing yourself for a ghost hunt</h2>\nWith a unit dedicated to helping you prepare for a ghost hunt, finding the best location, time and ways to conduct research, will help you create a successful hunt. You will be able to gain an insight into why airfields, abandoned buildings and hotels are some of the most haunted locations. Using this information why not take on the challenge of undergoing your own ghost hunt!\n<h2>Learn how to get rid of a ghost</h2>\nDo you have a ghost that you would like to get rid of? Then this course will explain ways in which you can do just that. From mirrors, salt and even hazelnuts, you?ll be sure to have those ghosts gone in no time!\n\nEnrol now on our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/ghost-hunting-2.html\">Ghost Hunting Level 2 </a>course!\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/ghost-hunting-2.html\">Take a look at our Ghost Hunting Level 2 course&gt;&gt;</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-09-16 10:30:01','2016-09-26 11:56:25',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=5951',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
