	(637,'5 Worst CV mistakes','5791-autosave-v1',NULL,NULL,'Making mistakes on your CV is easy, but it is extremely difficult to repair the damage once an employer receives it. So take a look at these 5 worst CV mistakes to make sure you don?t ruin your chances of achieving your dream job:\n<h2>Not making it relevant</h2>\nOne of the biggest mistakes you could make when putting together your CV is not targeting it to the job position you are applying for. Putting in key words that are relevant to the job position will allow your CV to stand out, especially if the employer scans through it. Explain how your skills can help you in that specific industry.\n<h2>Being sloppy</h2>\nSpelling, grammar, sending your CV in the wrong format and including negative information about yourself put recruitment managers off very quickly. These types of CV?s end up in the ?definite no? pile straight away. So make sure you proof read and edit continuously to help produce a perfect CV!\n<h2>Poor formatting</h2>\nA huge turn-off for employers is receiving a CV which isn?t very clear or easy to read. Did you know that on average recruiters spend 8.8 seconds reviewing a CV. So make sure you really sell yourself! With this in mind it is always a good idea to keep your CV brief with only the relevant information included in order for information to be absorbed quickly. You should definitely avoid using too many fonts or sizes and confusing layouts!\n<h2>Lack of evidence</h2>\nFailing to specifically evidence your skills and experiences can be a fatal mistake. Anyone can state that they have a skill, but explaining how they got it can give it a lot more credibility. So make sure you back up information!\n<h2>Too long</h2>\nEmployers do not have the time to read long CV?s, so keep it short! A good CV will consist of two pages ? no more and no less! Slimming down your CV will enable you to show off your communication skills and help you distinguish important information that is specific to the job position.\n\nBoost your CV with a qualification to make you stand out from the crowd!\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/contact_us.php\">Contact us </a>to know more about our courses.',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-10-13 11:39:41','2016-10-13 11:39:41',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/2016/10/13/5791-autosave-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(638,'5 Reasons why you should become a teaching assistant','5-reasons-become-teaching-assistant',NULL,NULL,'A teaching assistant role can be one of the most rewarding careers available, especially if you love making a difference to children\'s lives. So if you\'re thinking about studying to become a teaching assistant then check out these 5 reasons why you should:\n<h2>Help support students</h2>\nTeaching assistants make a real difference to a classroom. They support the learning of pupils and give one-to-one help with those that need extra assistance. So if you want to support the development of a child\'s learning and help them progress, then becoming a teacher assistant is perfect for you!\n<h2>Every day is different</h2>\nNo two days are ever the same when you?re a teaching assistant and sometimes you may even come across a few surprises. But this is what makes the job so unique. One day you could be helping pupils learn to read and another day you could be creating props and backdrops for school plays!\n<h2>Rewarding</h2>\nHelping students achieve their full potential can be very rewarding. Whether you?ve helped them learn to read or solve a maths problem, that proud moment you see the child?s face will make it all worthwhile!\n<h2>Flexible hours</h2>\nOne of the best benefits of becoming a teaching assistant is the hours. Working a school means you will only work school hours and get roughly 12 weeks holiday per year ? not many other positions allow you to have so much holiday time! This job is perfect if you have children within the education system, as you do not have to arrange child care for out of school hours.\n<h2>When you become a Teaching Assistant it\'s a stepping stone to further Qualifications</h2>\nIf your dream is to become a teacher, an assistant role is a great way to get your foot in the door. The experiences gained when you become a teaching assistant are invaluable so learn as much as you can!\n\nKick-start your career with a <a href=\"htt