	(709,'3 Reasons why studying history is important','3-reasons-why-studying-history-is-important',NULL,NULL,'It is very important we study history to help people learn from past mistakes and explore how the present came to be. So if you want gain an insight into our past or develop the knowledge needed to begin a career in this field, then one of our history courses are perfect for you. Here are 3 reasons why studying history is important:\n<h2>Helps us to understand people and societies</h2>\nWithout history, we cannot formulate laws or theories about human behaviour. It gives us vital evidence on how the society we live in today came to be. The past causes the future and therefore we must look for factors that took shape earlier. Only through our history can we grasp how things change.\n<h2>Provides identity</h2>\nHistory provides evidence about how families, groups, institutions and whole countries were formed and about how they have evolved while retaining cohesion. It allows you to gain an insight into your own family genealogy. Your family identity can then be established and confirmed.\n<h2>Importance on our own lives</h2>\nIt is important we hear the stories of those before us. We can then understand how the people before us lived. It is important for us to hear these stories, preserve them and then pass them down to those after us. Things are then not forgotten.\n\nEnrol now on one of our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/history_courses.html\">history courses</a>!\n\n<a class=\"blog-cta\" href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/history_courses.html\">Take a look at our history courses</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2016-11-18 16:26:33','2016-11-18 16:26:33',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=6212',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
