	(862,'5 Instant confidence boosters','5-instant-confidence-boosters',NULL,NULL,'When students have a negative attitude towards their studies this is normally reflected in their grades. So to make sure you don?t fall into this trap, take a look at these 5 instant confidence boosters:\n<h2>Empower yourself with knowledge</h2>\nBy boosting your knowledge, you?ll be able to build your confidence in the field you work in. Exploring things that you struggle with or not quite sure of will help you complete your tasks easier.\n<h2>Set goals</h2>\nBreaking down large goals into smaller ones, will help with the progression of your course. You?ll be able to see that you are heading the right direction, making your studying more enjoyable. <a href=\"https://blog.openstudycollege.com/how-to-achieve-your-goals/\">Find out how you can achieve your own goals</a>.\n<h2>Think positive</h2>\nHaving a positive attitude will help keep your body relaxed and make it easier for you to concentrate. If your studying isn?t going as planned, take a break and come back to it. Focus on the reason for your studies and try not to get stressed out.\n<h2>Prepare your studies</h2>\nCreating a study plan can not only help you get organised, it will also enable you to feel confident your studies are going to plan. Avoid late night cramming sessions and get your learningon track with a planned schedule. Just what you need to feel positive about your studies. <a href=\"https://blog.openstudycollege.com/make-study-plan/\">Take a look at how to create a study plan.</a>\n<h2>Do something you?ve been procrastinating on</h2>\nIf you?ve got a task on your to-do-list that you?ve been putting off for ages, get it done. The longer it?s left, the longer you?ll be thinking about it. When you have, you?ll feel great.\n\nBy following these 5 confidence boosters, you can make your studying easier and achieve those higher grades.',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-03-10 11:03:56','2017-03-10 11:07:46',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege