	(882,'Why it\'s important for us to know about eating disorders','important-eating-disorders',NULL,NULL,'Eating disorders are becoming increasingly common with 1.6 million people in the UK being affected. People can be affected in different ways including severely reducing the amount of food they eat, or eating unusually large amounts and are extremely concerned about their weight or shape. Here?s whyit\'s important for us to know about them:\n<h2>Give advice</h2>\nBy learning more about eating disorders you will be able to advise people about how to improve their diet and work out a progress plan to get them back to good health.\n<h2>Know the types of disorders</h2>\nWith the wide range of eating disorders such as anorexia nervosa, bulimia nervosa, and binge eating, it is important to know the different treatments associated to each. Whether it?s to improve your health or someone else?s, it?s good to learn how you can make a difference.\n<h2>Understand the effects</h2>\nEating disorders are very serious and can even be life-threatening. Which is why understanding about the effects is very important. Recognising the psychological, social and biological effects will enable you to understand what someone is going through.\n<h2>Identify who can be affected</h2>\nAnyone can be effected by eating disorders, from children to the elderly. Statistics show that in the UK, they affect 14-25 year olds the most, this can be due to a number of reasons including the media, low self-esteem and social issues.\n\nDevelop your knowledge and enrol on our<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/understanding-eating-disorders-2.html\">Level 2 course</a>today!\n\n<a class=\"blog-cta\" href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/understanding-eating-disorders-2.html\">Take a look at our Understanding Eating Disorders Level 2 course</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-03-23 09:38:30','2017-03-23 09:38:30',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=6596',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
