	(920,'3 Reasons to start studying Psychology with us','4926-autosave-v1',NULL,NULL,'Psychology is the study of mind and behaviour. It is a science, which allows psychologists to study human behaviour by observing, measuring and testing, then arriving at conclusions. It is interesting for us to find out what makes us tick and how the information we discover can help solve major problems in society. Here are 3 reasons why you should study psychology:\n<h2>1. Learn about human behaviour</h2>\nUnderstanding someone?s behaviour is a great way to explore how the mind works. You will be able to discover how millions of people are affected by disorders of the brain and nervous system including: Alzheimer?s, Parkinson?s disease, strokes and traumatic brain injuries. In addition, find out the answers to fascinating questions such as:\n<ul>\n	<li>Why we feel more energetic in the morning?</li>\n	<li>Why we try to analyse our dreams?</li>\n	<li>How hypnosis works?</li>\n	<li>Why we continuously learn throughout our lives?</li>\n	<li>How do we remember?</li>\n</ul>\nPsychology is an interesting subject and can help you understand your own life and behaviour.\n<h2>2. Explore research methods</h2>\nA major part of psychology is methodology. This is because it is used to conduct research and help describe and measure human behaviour. There are a number of methods that psychologists use. Some of these include: observations, experiments, case studies and survey?s. These are used to gather data, format theories, test predictions and interpret results.\n<h2>3. Investigate psychology in society</h2>\nGordon Allport a famous Psychologist defines social psychology as:\n<blockquote>\"Understanding and explaining how the thought, feeling and behaviour of individuals are influenced by the actual, imagined or implied presence of other human beings\" (1985). ? Gordon Allport</blockquote>\nYou will be able to discover the factors that lead us to behave in a given way in the presence of others. You can then see how this refers to your own life and others.\n\n<h2>Start</h2>\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/psychology_courses.html\" class=\"blog-cta\">Learn more about human behaviour and mind in one of our Psychology courses</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-03-06 12:54:28','2017-03-06 12:54:28',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/4926-autosave-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(921,'5 Reasons why you should start your own business','6330-autosave-v1',NULL,NULL,'Would you like to start your own business?\n\nHave you dreamed about owning your own business for years, but finally want to turn it into a reality? Then you can! Here?s 5 reasons why you should take the first step towards entrepreneurial success - here\'s why you should start your own business today:\n<h2>Independence and flexibility</h2>\nOne of themain benefits of owning your own business is the flexibility that comes with it. You decide when you work, set your own hours, what you wear and when you go on holiday. It will also enable you to spend more time with your family.\n<h2>Follow your passion</h2>\nIf there?s something that you enjoy and have an interest in, then setting up your own business can be very satisfying. Following your passion won?t feel like work and no one has more pride in what they do than business owners.\n<h2>Success</h2>\nThe one thing business owners aim for is success. It opens up the possibility of making more money than you could make as an employee. You decide where your profits go. Maybe you want to give some to a charity? Personally give it back to the community? Or help you provide a living?\n<h2>Choose who works for you</h2>\nYou will have the opportunity to select who you work with. Choosing a skilled workforce will make your business more likely to succeed. You can pick people that are most suitable to work in your business and you think would fit in well. Knowing that your passion has provided them with a living, can be very satisfying.\n<h2>Take on new challenges</h2>\nThe boredom of working in a dull office job is one of the biggest reasons why you should start your own business. If you hate sitting in an office job doing the same thing every day, then by starting your own business you can create a new challenge, something that will inspire you. One day will never be the same, it will be packed with variety and help you learn something new every day.\n\n<a class=\"blog-cta\" href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/starting-your-own-business.html\">Take a look at our Level 3 Starting your own business course</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-03-06 13:07:03','2017-03-06 13:07:03',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/6330-autosave-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
