	(935,'What are \'T Level\' qualifications?','t-level-qualifications',NULL,NULL,'The modern society are all very familiar with the concept of A Levels.\n\nYou go to school to study your GCSEs before progressing into sixth form or college to study your A Levels. According to the Department for Education, A Levels may soon be in harsh competition with - and perhaps even replaced by - T Levels. But what exactly are they...?\n<h2>What are \'T Levels\'?</h2>\nTechnical Levels also known as T Levels are aimed at establishing parity between academic and technical routes. 15 new pathways will be developed between now and 2022, which will help students progress into employment. They will be considered as the new alternative to A Levels.\n<blockquote>?Investing in skills and education is the key to inclusive growth ? to an economy that works for everyone?\n\n? Philip Hammond,\nChancellor of the Exchequer</blockquote>\nThe idea behind T Levels was to create a qualification with the student and employer in mind. T Levels have been developed with employers as a 2-yearcollege qualificationwith the inclusion of a 3-month industry placement. They allow you to gain knowledgeable experience in the industry of your choice.\n<h2>When can I study a \'T Level\'?</h2>\nThe first T Levels will be available for teaching in September 2019 with the rest aiming to be in place by 2022. Some of the 15 sectors which these qualifications will cater for include childcare and education, hair and beauty, business and administrative and construction.\n<h2>Why study a \'T Level\'?</h2>\nThese qualifications will allow students to go onto a Level 4 or 5 technical education programme. They will also be beneficial for those wanting to gain entry into university or looking to start an apprenticeship.\n\nThe government is constantly improving the education system to reflect the way we as a society learn. T Levels are a good representation of this, and will be a successful component of education in the years to come.',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-03-24 12:06:43','2018-11-12 11:58:14',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=6729',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(936,'Budget 2017 ? The facts about \'T-Level\' qualifications','6729-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Last week, Chancellor Philip Hammond gave his Budget speech in the House of Commons. This is his first and last Spring budget since the Brexit referendum. And has made some important changes in the education industry ? particularly introducing new \'T-Level\' qualifications. But what exactly are they?\n<h2>What are \'T-Level\'?</h2>\nTechnical Levels also known as T-Levels are aimed at establishing parity between academic and technical routes for 16-19 year olds. 15 new pathways will be developed between now and 2022, which will help students progress into employment. They will be considered as the new alternative to A-Levels.\n<blockquote>?Investing in skills and education is the key to inclusive growth ? to an economy that works for everyone? ? Mr Hammond</blockquote>\n<h2>When can I study a \'T-Level\'?</h2>\nThe first T-Levels will be available for teaching in September 2019 with the rest aiming to be in place by 2022. Some of the 15 sectors which these qualifications will cater for include: childcare and education, hair and beauty, business and administrative and construction.\n<h2>Why study a \'T-Level\'?</h2>\nThese qualifications will allow students to go onto a Level 4 or 5 technical education programme. They will also be beneficial for those wanting to gain entry into university or looking to start an apprenticeship.',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-03-10 12:45:45','2017-03-10 12:45:45',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/6729-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(937,'5 Reasons why you should study dog training','5709-autosave-v1',NULL,NULL,'Are you interested in learning everything you need to know about man?s best friend? Do you want to become a dog trainer? Maybe you want to develop your skills to train your canine? Then here are 5 reasons why you should study dog training:\n<h2>Explore the history of dog training</h2>\nYou will be able to find out why and when dog training came about and how they assisted men in combat in the First and Second World War. Explore how changes in jobs and busier lifestyles now mean that dogs have to be trained in order for them to behave when they are left at home alone.\n<h2>Understand a dog?s body language</h2>\nThis module will enable you to learn what a dog is trying to tell you using their body language. Although dogs use sounds and signals to communicate with us, the majority of information comes from their body language. You will be able to become an expert in understanding when a dog is relaxed, curious, aggressive, fearful, stressed and worried!\n<h2>Learn how to teach a dog new tricks</h2>\nThis fun and exciting topic area will allow you to develop your knowledge in the different types of tricks you can learn a dog. Discover the use of clicker training and how to use positive and negative reinforcement in training. Maybe you will be able to teach your own dog how to beg, paw, back-up, turn around, fetch and lots more amazing tricks!\n<h2>Recognise the various types of dog sports</h2>\nYes that?s right dogs have their own sports! You will gain an insight into the UK Rally, obedience, agility and tracking and training. Explore how dogs are trained to jump, travel through tunnels and navigate their way onto a range of walkways. Perhaps you could train your dog to take part in these sports!\n<h2>Discover how to communicate with a dog</h2>\nIt is vital for you to know how to communicate with a dog, whether it?s your own or someone else?s. Investigate the importance of using a mix of signs, eye contact, body movements and hand signals and identify various learning theories that can help you understand a dog?s behaviour.\n\nWhether you have a new canine friend or want to develop your knowledge to become a dog trainer, this course covers everything you need to know!\n\nStudy<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/dog-training-3.html\"> dog training</a>today!\n\n<a class=\"blog-cta\" href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/dog-training-3.html\">Take a look at our Dog Training Level 3 course&gt;&gt;</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-03-13 12:57:32','2017-03-13 12:57:32',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/5709-autosave-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
