	(1013,'3 Reasons why you should learn French','6377-autosave-v1',NULL,NULL,'Did you know that over 220 million people speak French and it is the second most widely learned language after English? Which is why learning French is a valuable skill to have. Here?s 3 reasons why you should learn French:\n<h2>Help achieve a new job</h2>\nMany UK businesses now work with clients, partners and customers in France, so having the ability of speaking French can give you a competitive advantage. Candidates that have language skills are a hit for employers and can make all the difference in achieving your dream job.\n<h2>Personal enjoyment</h2>\nIf you want to challenge yourself and learn a new skill, then a language is great to do just that! Not only can it help enrich your mind, but it can also open up a wide range of opportunities. If you have French relatives and friends, you will be able to communicate with them easier and show themyou\'re interested in their culture.\n<h2>Easier when travelling</h2>\nDo you love visiting France? Then how easy would it be if you could actually speak the language! With France attracting more than 79,5 million visitors a year and being one of the world?s top tourist destination, gaining the ability to speak French can help you understand where places are, communicate with people, read menus and lots more!\n\nLearn French with our lan\n\n<a class=\"blog-cta\" href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/linguaphone-french.html\">Take a look at our French Beginner ? Advanced course</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-03-31 13:02:10','2017-03-31 13:02:10',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/6377-autosave-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(1014,'3 Reasons why you should study Primatology','6452-autosave-v1',NULL,NULL,'Do you find learning about primates, including gorillas, orangutans, chimpanzees, and lemurs fascinating and want to know more? Maybe you?d love to gain the knowledge to begin your journey as a primatologist? Then here are 3 reasons why you should study primatology:\n<h2>Gain an insight into the evolution of primates</h2>\nOur Level 3 course will allow you to explore the existence of primates and learn about where they originated from. It will also enable you to gain a fascinating insight into the primate family tree, investigating the different stages including old monkeys, new monkeys and great apes.\n<h2>Explore old and new world monkeys</h2>\nYou will be able to understand the global distributions of old and new monkeys and understand why they live where they do. This interesting module is great if you\'d like to learn about different monkey family types and want to gain an insight into their unique characteristics and behaviours.\n<h2>Develop your knowledge about prosimians</h2>\nWith a unit dedicated to prosimians you will explore the geography and habitats of their main origin ? Madagascar. In this module, you can investigate the different types of primates belonging to the Strepsirrhini and Haplorhini suborder. Here you will be able to gain a fascinating insight into lemurs, Tarsiers and much more!\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/primatology-3.html\">Primatology Level 3 course!</a>\n\n<a class=\"blog-cta\" href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/primatology-3.html\">Take a look at our Primatology Level 3 course</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-03-31 13:08:21','2017-03-31 13:08:21',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/6452-autosave-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(1015,'5 Reasons why you should become a nurse','6458-autosave-v1',NULL,NULL,'Would you love to become a nurse? Do you want to make a difference to someone?s life? Then here?s 5 reasons why you should:\n<h2>Make a difference</h2>\nThe role of a nurse can be very satisfying. You will have to care for your patients and provide them with the help and support they need. By spending a lot of time with people and building relationships, you will be able to make a real difference to their lives.\n<h2>Industry demand</h2>\nThe demand for nurses in the UK is larger than ever. Last year there were 23,443 nursing vacancies and this shortage has predicted to continue. So now it is a great time to kick-start your career in nursing.\n<h2>Work variety</h2>\nThe duties of a nurse vary day to day ? there will never be a dull moment. You could be administering medication one day then assisting a doctor during surgery the next.\n<h2>Stepping stone</h2>\nIf you have your sights set on a higher positioned role within the health care industry, then becoming a nurse is a great way to get a foot in the door. By progressing and taking on more responsibility you will be able to achieve your dream career.\n<h2>Work in an environment to suit you</h2>\nBecoming a nurse doesn?t mean that you have to work in a hospital. You can work in a variety of environments, including: a care home, school and patients home. Which means you can find a nursing job that suits you.\n\nKick-start your career today with our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/principles-of-nursing-practice-3.html\">Level 3 Principles of Nursing Practice course</a>!\n\n<a class=\"blog-cta\" href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/principles-of-nursing-practice-3.html\">Enrol now on our Principles of Nursing Practice Level 3 course</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-03-31 13:10:31','2017-03-31 13:10:31',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/6458-autosave-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(1016,'3 Reasons why you should study IGCSE English','6609-autosave-v1',NULL,NULL,'Do you want to achieve an internationally recognised qualification in English? Then explore how to write to describe, inform and persuade and study IGCSE English. Here?s 3 reasons why you should:\n<h2>Go onto further education</h2>\nThe IGCSE English is an internationally renowned qualification that is recognised worldwide by universities, schools and employers as equivalent in status and academic rigour to a UK GCSE. So if you want to go onto further education at A-Level or BTEC Level then an IGCSE in English is perfect for you.\n<h2>Explore different types of passages</h2>\nWith a unit dedicated to passages, you?ll be able to gain an insight into letters, reports, journals and much more. Explore how to create some of the amazing affects authors use in their writing and learn how to develop some of your own ideas in your writing.\n<h2>Gain an insight into how to write</h2>\nOur IGCSE English course will enable you to gain a fascinating insight into how to express your feelings and opinions in your own writing. You?ll also learn how to write to explain, inform and persuade, using the appropriate vocabulary.\n\nEnrol today on our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/igcse-english-first-language.html\">IGCSE English First Language course</a>!\n\n<a class=\"blog-cta\" href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/igcse-english-first-language.html\">Take a look at our IGCSE English First Language course</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-03-31 13:15:09','2017-03-31 13:15:09',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/6609-autosave-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(1017,'5 Tips to achieve your goals this April','4959-autosave-v1',NULL,NULL,'Do you feel like the year is going too fast? It?s already April and you are still stuck in the same mind-set doing the same thing. Then stop?this is your chance to make a change and achieve those important goals that you\'ve always wanted. Here are 5 tips on how toachieve your goals:\n<h2>Decide what you want</h2>\nThe first thing you need to do is think about what you want to achieve. This can be either a big or small change - it is up to you! By taking your time to think about what you want is an important first step for helping you succeed. Do you want a distinction in your course? Do you want to achieve your dream job? You decide what you want! You then want to ask yourself why these are important to you and determine if these goals are realistic.\n<h2>Make a plan</h2>\nYou should start by brainstorming together thoughts about the following:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Your ideal future</li>\n 	<li>Qualities you admire in others</li>\n 	<li>Things that could be done better</li>\n 	<li>Things you want to learn more about</li>\n 	<li>Habits you want to improve</li>\n</ul>\nThese will get you thinking about how you can improve yourself and get you on your way to achieving your desired goals.\n<h2>Make your goals SMART</h2>\nAn effective way to assess your goals is to make them smart:\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong>S</strong>pecific</li>\n 	<li><strong>M</strong>easurable</li>\n 	<li><strong>A</strong>chievable</li>\n 	<li><strong>R</strong>elevant</li>\n 	<li><strong>T</strong>ime-bounded</li>\n</ul>\nIf you have more than one goal you should rank these in order of importance. This will then show you which ones are the most meaningful to you.\n<h2>Dedicate your time</h2>\nTo achieve your goals you will need to put a lot of hard work and time into making them a reality. You should think about how long you expect it will take you to achieve themand when you want it to be completed. If you are truly committed to your goal you will need to dedicate your time on it. You should do this by building your efforts into a daily routine and scheduling your time to work on your goals every day.\n<h2>Track your performance</h2>\nWhen you are working towards your goal you should keep track of your progress. You could do this by keeping a journal, using an app or making a note in a diary. You will then be able to notice your improvements and study your performance, which will help you stay motivated. Use positive and negative reinforcement in order to push yourself to achieve your goals.\n\nReach for your dreams and start achieving your goals today!',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-04-03 13:39:31','2017-04-03 13:39:31',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/4959-autosave-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
