	(1033,'3 Reasons why you should learn about the principles of nursing','3-reasons-learn-principles-nursing',NULL,NULL,'Do you want to begin a career in nursing? Then what better time to kick-start your career than on International Nurses Day! Enrol today on our Level 3 course and boost your skills in the principles of nursing. Here?s 3 reasons why you should:\n<h2>Understand key nursing procedures</h2>\nSome of the main duties that are completed by a nurse include taking pulses, blood pressure readings and breathing rates. Our Level 3 course will allow you to gain an insight into this and much more. You?ll understand how breathing rates are observed and measured and explore the process in undertaking urinalysis.\n<h2>Learn how to communicate with patients</h2>\nCommunication skills are essential in a nursing career. Knowing how to communicate with patients, family and friends and the public is very important. That?s why our course has a unit dedicated to the key models of communications, barriers and methods. Just what you need feel confident in communicating to others.\n<h2>Explore the psychology of care</h2>\nNurses have the task of helping patient?s well-being through their recovery, coping with disease and long term conditions. Making a difference to people?s lives is a daily task for nurses and they have to concentrate on the different states of health and well-being, including: physical, mental, social, emotional and societal. Our course will share the theory on how to do just this.\n\nEnrol today on our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/principles-of-nursing-practice-3.html\">Principles of Nursing Practice Level 3 course</a> and kick-start your career!\n\n<a class=\"blog-cta\" href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/principles-of-nursing-practice-3.html\">Take a look at our Principles of Nursing Practice Level 3 course</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-05-12 08:56:31','2017-05-12 08:56:31',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=7005',1,1,1,0,0