	(1054,'What are ABE qualifications? Everything you need to know about ABE qualifications and courses','7043-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Having been around for over 40 years, ABE qualifications enablepeople from all over the world to gain the most up to date and dynamic skills on the market. Here?s everything you need to know about ABE qualifications and courses:\n<h2>What are ABE Qualifications?</h2>\nEstablished in 1973 ABE provide high quality qualifications all around the world in areas including entrepreneurship, business start-up, business management, marketing, human resources, travel, tourism and hospitality management.\n\nThese Ofqual regulated qualifications reinforce high quality innovative education and work towards inspiring and empowering learners. Over 1.5 million people have improved their skills with an ABE qualification, where many have gone on to own a successful business. They are recognised by colleges, universities, employers and governments all around the world.\n<h2>Who can study an ABE qualification?</h2>\nWith the help of distance learning these qualifications are accessible in over 100 countries and this number is continually growing. Studying at home allows students to easily access ABE courses digitally across their devices, anywhere, at any time.\n<h2>Can I use these for entry into university?</h2>\nYes! ABE qualifications are accepted by over 80 different universities. Offering a range of Level courses means finding the perfect qualification to suit your abilities is easy. Just what you need to fast-track onto a degree course.\n<h2>Why study an ABE?</h2>\nAn ABE qualification is great for gaining a Ofqual recognised qualification in the business or travel and tourism industry. Having this qualification on your CV will help you boost your chances of achieving your desired career and can also help top up your university degree. These qualifications will enable you to gain the most up to date and dynamic skills on the market.\n\nTake a look a