	(1066,'What are the benefits of a new qualification?','7060-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Deciding to undertake a new qualification is a big decision, so you probably want to know what the benefits of a new qualification are. You may want to boost your career progression, or learn something new to take a step towards the career you\'ve always wanted. C.S. Lewis once said:\n\n<em>?You are never too old to set another goal, or to dream another dream?</em>\n\nWhatever your reason, Open Study College offers the flexibility to fit studying around your lifestyle, and help you to achieve your goals with a new qualification. It?s never too late to learn something new, or choose a new career path.\n<h2>So, what are the benefits?</h2>\n<h3>Enhance your C.V.</h3>\nA new qualification can help you to stand out when an employer has looked at numerous CVs already. It demonstrates to potential employers that you are enthusiastic about your work, and have the drive to learn and grow in your role.\n<h3>Boost your confidence</h3>\nIf you want to increaseyour knowledge and skills in your existing role, then a new qualification is a great opportunity to do so. Or if youwant learn something new, a qualification allows you to develop your foundation of knowledge to progress into a newcareer.\n<h3>Increase your salary</h3>\nAchieving a new qualification gives you the opportunity to speak to your boss about a potential promotionand pay rise. If that?s not an option, it gives you a great reason to apply for new positions at a higher level than your current role and achieve the salary you deserve.\n<h3>Step into a new career</h3>\nYou may have always dreamed of a certain career, but never had the opportunity to study for the qualification that could get you there. With a distance learning course from Open Study College you can now start studying for a career you really want.\n<h3>Further study</h3>\nOur A-Level courses offer the UCAS points you need to get into university and achieve your degree. Alternatively, you may have studied a level 2 course and you want to progress your studies further and achieve a level 3 qualification. Open Study College offer a wide range of level 2 and 3 courses.\n\nIf you?re ready to take that important first step towards studying a new qualification then <strong><a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/contact_us.php\">get in touch</a></strong>! For more information about the courses we offer visit <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/\"><strong>our website</strong></a>, or call a Student Adviser on <strong>03300 563100</strong>.',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-05-11 11:45:21','2017-05-11 11:45:21',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/7060-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(1067,'How have Open Study College helped over 60,000 people?','open-study-college-helped-60000-people',NULL,NULL,'Later this year at Open Study College, we will celebrate our 10<sup>th</sup> anniversary. Since starting in 2007, we have helped over 60,000 people to progress in their careers, or study something new and successfully change careers. Here\'s the ways we helped those 60,000 people?\n<h2><strong>Affordable</strong></h2>\nOur courses are competitively priced, and we offer our students the option to pay for their course using our low monthly payment plan. Many students have taken advantage of this plan and chosen to spread the cost of their course. This allows our studentsto start their studies straight away instead of saving before starting their studies.\n<h2><strong>Award winning tutor support</strong></h2>\nOur experienced tutors offer unlimited support and advice to our students, helping them to successfully complete their course. Our tutors have received industry recognition too! We have been nominated four times for Tutor of the Year, which we have also won once. We were also awarded Excellence in Tutor Support 2016, a real testament to the support our course tutors provide.\n<h2><strong>Trusted, independent qualifications</strong></h2>\nOur courses are accredited by independent awarding bodies to give our students peace of mind that they are studying for a qualification they can trust. The qualifications we offer are accredited by the likes of AAT, CACHE and CompTIA.\n<h2><strong>Externally verified</strong></h2>\nOpen Study College are verified by the British Institute for Learning and Development Council and the Open and Distance Learning Quality Council. This means that our students can feel confident that they?re studying with one of the UK?s leading and most trusted distance learning providers.\n<h2><strong>Great extras</strong></h2>\nOur students are offered a free CV writing serviceto help their CV stand out from the crowd and secure their dream job. We also provide our students with a free NUS extra card, for exclusive discounts at their favourite high street outlets.\n<h2><strong>Study anywhere, anytime</strong></h2>\nThe days of being confined to a classroom from 9-4 are gone. With our distance learning courses you can study from the comfort of your own home or on the go. You can also fit the course around work and childcare commitments, and study when it suits you.\n<h2><strong>Something for everyone</strong></h2>\nAt Open Study College, we offer a wide variety of courses so there truly is something for everyone. With over 450 courses available, our courses range from Makeup Artistry to Bookkeeping, Childcare and Education to A Levels.\n<h2><strong>Increased confidence and salary</strong></h2>\nA new qualification will certainly increase both your salary and your confidence. A qualification that builds on your knowledge and skills issure to boost confidence. And with the extra knowledge under your belt, your earning potential will most likely increase too.\n\nIf you?re interested in finding out more about the courses we offer, and how we can help you progress or achieve a career you love, visit <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/\">our website</a> or call a Student Adviser on <strong>03300 563100</strong> today.\n\n<a class=\"blog-cta\" href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/contact_us.php\">Contact us</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-05-30 08:20:59','2017-05-30 08:20:59',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=7064',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
