	(1093,'Reasons to choose a career as an Aromatherapist','7109-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Has a career as an Aromatherapist ever interested you? If so, why not take a chance and study a course in Aromatherapy? This week is Aromatherapy Awareness Week so what better time to learn more about the career. Here are our reasons to choose a career asan Aromatherapist?\n\n<strong>Firstly, what is an Aromatherapist? </strong>\n\nAromatherapists use infusions and natural oils to promote emotional well being and better health in their clients. Day-to-day responsibilities of an Aromatherapist include consultations with clients, blending oils and applying oils via full or partial body massage. You may also refer clients to a doctor when necessary.\n<h3>Why should I become an Aromatherapist?</h3>\n<h4>Income</h4>\nAs a self-employed, qualified Aromatherapist you can expect to charge anywhere between 25 and 70 an hour. Of course, there will be business fees to pay too.\n<h4>Flexibility</h4>\nYou can work part-time or full-time depending on your other commitments. You will also set your own schedule and choose the hours you work. It is important to keep in mind that you will need a degree of flexibility to accommodate your clients.\n<h4>Opportunities</h4>\nA qualified Aromatherapist has several employment options open to them, such as the following:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Self-employment</li>\n 	<li>Health spas</li>\n 	<li>Private clinics</li>\n 	<li>Offering therapy at hospitals or hospices</li>\n</ul>\nAn experienced Aromatherapist could offer a mobile service visiting clients in their homes, or set up their own clinic. Another option is to offer additional therapies such as reflexology or massage to boost your client base and income.\n<h4>Passion</h4>\nAromatherapists are passionate about their work, and that passion can be channelled into improving their client?s well being. The same passion can also be used in their everyday lives, helping them to lead healthier lifestyles and implement natural self-care.\n\nFor more information about our Aromatherapy course, go to <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/ncfe-aromatherapy-osc.html\"><strong>our website</strong></a> or call a Student Adviser on <strong>03300 100563</strong>.',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-05-24 15:48:02','2017-05-24 15:48:02',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/7109-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
