d development plays a big part in an engineer?s role. Whether you are an apprentice working towards a qualification at college or university, or a graduate working towards becoming chartered or attending management courses, the opportunities to grow and develop in your career are continuous. Employers want to see their employees succeed and move up the career ladder.\n<h3>Travel Opportunities</h3>\nMany engineers are expected to travel regularly as part of their job. You could need to visit a supplier?s premises in another country, travel to another city to see a construction site, or attend a conference or training day.\n<h3>Make a difference</h3>\nThere are examples of great engineering all around us. The cars we drive are safer, mobile phones have become central to daily life, medical testing has become more accurate? whatever route you choose to take your career down, you are sure to develop innovations that benefit society. In essence, engineers protect our planet, reduce poverty and save lives!\n<h2>How can Open Study College help?</h2>\nIf you?re looking to get into university to study engineering then we can help you. We offer a great range of A Levels, including Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry, that count towards your UCAS points. If you would like to know more about the A Levels we offer go to <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/a-level\">our website</a> or call 03300 563100.\n\n&nbsp;',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-06-13 12:44:08','2017-06-13 12:44:08',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/7190-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
