	(1148,'','7220-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'<blockquote>\n<h3>?If I could be qualified to do this, in essence, it would save the company money and essentially give me another ?qualified? string to my bow.?</h3>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Growing responsibilities</h2>\nWorking as a P.A. to the Managing Director, Helen found herself taking on more and more responsibility. She was juggling everything from HR and Training, to Accounts and Wages. Having studied Accounts and Bookkeeping at school, Helen was familiar with some of the concepts but lacked the knowledge to efficiently complete the purchasing, sales invoicing, and payments, etc. on a daily basis.\n<h2>Goals</h2>\nHelen and her boss decided to make life a little easier in the long term by improving Helen?s Accounting knowledge and skills. Helen chose to study an AAT Accounting Level 2 and 3 course with the goal of becoming more efficient in her work. Currently, Helen?s boss outsources finalising the accounts and putting it all onto Sage to an external Accountant. Helen was also very keen to learn accounting jargon to help her understand what the Accountant is talking about.\n<h2>Further Study</h2>\nImpressively, Helen?s studies moved at a very quick pace. Having started her level 2 course in September 2016, she completed it in May 2017. Students are given a year to complete their course, so it is a great achievement for Helen to complete hers in 9 months whilst working part-time. Demonstrating her enthusiasm for developing her accounting knowledge, and achieving her qualification, Helen has thrown herself into studying the level 3 course:\n<blockquote>\n<h3><em>?Level 3 is a natural progression, and will allow me to take on board more of the accounting process to lessen the need to outsource this?</em></h3>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Why Open Study College?</h2>\nHelen chose to study with Open Study College because they ?stood out from the other training providers? that she looked at. Both Helen and her boss were impressed with 