	(1287,'5 Reasons why you should study A-Level Business Studies','6489-autosave-v1',NULL,NULL,'Our Business Studies A-Level is a recognised qualification and is the equivalent to the one you would study at a traditional school or college. A-Levels can lead to university, further study, training, or work, which is why you should study a home learning A-Level Business Studies course. Here?s why:\n<h2>Develop how to market a business</h2>\nOur A-Level Business Studies will enable you to understand how to meet customer needs and gain an insight into different markets. After studying this module, you will be able to plan a marketing strategy, which will help a business meet its maximum profit potential.\n<h2>Explore business activity in a global context</h2>\nIn this interesting unit, you will be able to investigate how and why businesses trade on a global scale. You will look intoglobal competitiveness andthe growth rate of the UK economy compared to emerging economies.\n<h2>Understand how to manage business activities</h2>\nYou will be able to develop your knowledge in raising and managing finance and measuring a business?s performance. With this information,you\'ll understand the importance of using resources efficiently, so goods and services can be deliveredto a high quality.\n<h2>Gain entry into university</h2>\nIf you?re looking to go onto a business degree, then an A-Level in Business Studies is perfect for you. It will allow you to achieve those all-important UCAS points you need for entry into university.\n<h2>Kick-start your career</h2>\nBoosting your knowledge within the world of business can help you kick-start your dream career, whether you would love to set up your own business, work in marketing, human resources or become a business manager.\n\nKick-start your prospects with our<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/a-level-business-studies-2015.html\"> A-Level Business Studies</a>!\n\n<a class=\"blog-cta\" href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/a-level-business-studies-2015.html\">Take a look at our A-Level Business Studies</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-09-11 11:41:17','2017-09-11 11:41:17',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/6489-autosave-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(1288,'Passionate about reading? Study A Level English Literature','passionate-reading-study-a-level-english-literature',NULL,NULL,'Do you enjoy nothing more than getting stuck into a good book? Would you love a career in Journalism or Teaching? Well, you are going to love A Level English Literature!\n<h2>Who is A Level English Literature for?</h2>\nA Level English Literature is perfect for anyone who loves reading, poetry, or going to the theatre. You will have the opportunity to immerse yourself in new experiences and characters, and take on new perspectives. Universities also highly value an A Level English Literature qualification, because it is a notoriously difficult subject that boosts your analytical and interpretive skills.\n<h2>What will I study?</h2>\nThe course covers 4 different study areas:\n<ol>\n 	<li><strong>Drama</strong> ? you will study two dramatic comedies, Twelfth Night by William Shakespeare and The important of being earnest by Oscar Wilde.</li>\n 	<li><strong>Prose</strong> ? during this course you will study the following two prose works; Frankenstein by Mary Shelley, and The Handmaid?s Tale by Margaret Atwood.</li>\n 	<li><strong>Poetry</strong> ? this course covers a selection of poems, a collection of post-2000 poetry, and another collection of poems from T.S. Eliot.</li>\n 	<li><strong>Coursework</strong> ? You will also need to complete a piece of coursework that compares Emily Bront?s Wuthering Heights and The Bloody Chamber by Angela Carter.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>What can I study next?</h2>\nThe knowledge and skills gained from your A Level English Literature course prepares you for several courses at degree level. Firstly, and most obviously, the course will be good preparation for an English Literature degree? but that?s not all! An A Level in English Literature is also very useful if you are keen to study degrees in creative writing, politics, media and communications, and journalism.\n<h2>What about my future career?</h2>\nAfter studying A Level English Literature, and then going on to possibly study at university, you will be ready for several careers, including:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Teaching</li>\n 	<li>Publishing</li>\n 	<li>Media</li>\n 	<li>Social Work</li>\n 	<li>Law</li>\n 	<li>Public Sector</li>\n</ul>\nIf you would like to find out more about our A Level English Literature course, go to our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/a-level-english-literature.html\">website</a> or call a Student Adviser on <strong>03300 563100</strong> today!',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-09-15 12:56:35','2017-09-15 12:56:35',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=7491',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL);
