om dinner till bedtime it?s family time only, no work, no emails, no study.\n\nI can tuck them up in bed at night knowing that I was 100% there for them.\n\n<strong>Don?t quit</strong>\n\nYou?re a parent, so you?ve got over the fact you can?t just quit, and oh my, there are days that are sent to test you, but always know that tomorrow or the day after will be easier, keep taking those tiny steps forward and don?t give up on yourself.\n\nI promise it will be worth it in the end.',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-10-11 12:16:40','2017-10-11 12:16:40',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/7603-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(1344,'Working with Children | Study Childcare, Health and Education','working-with-children',NULL,NULL,'<h2><strong>Working with children</strong></h2>\nThe children of today are tomorrows future. Therefore, working with children duringtheir early years and their schooling is a rewarding career. There is a wide selection of career choices working with children, across teaching and education, healthcare and social care. Another career choice could include leisure - maybe running children\'s activities, or practising law as a family lawyer. In addition working in the charity and voluntary sector, supporting children through difficult times, may be where your interest lies. Even working in the public services sector as a children\'s librarian, the possibilities are endless.\n\nPerhaps working with older children, as a youth worker? Helping teenagersget throughdifficulties and navigate their way into adulthood? Or work in a school setting as a teaching assistant, mentor or a careers adviser yourself. The healthcare sector provides careers such as children\'s nursing, therapist and health visitors. Great if you are passionate about working with new mothers and their babies.\n<h2><strong>What to study</strong></h2>\nWhatever career you decide on, the best way to begin is to work towards the right qualifications. If you are at the start of your journey, changing direction or already working with children, Open Study College has a variety of <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/childcare_courses.html\">childcare courses ranging from introductory level through to Level 3,</a> to cater to all student requirements.\n\nNursing, Teaching and Social Work are all graduate jobs and require a relevant degree. Students can earn the UCAS points they need to get to university with our<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/a-level\"> A-Level courses.</a>If you want to keep your options open by studying vocational courses, the <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/cache\">Council for Awards in Care, Health and Education (CACHE) qualifications</a> are available via Open Study College from entry Level 1 to Level 3. The perfect starting point in your study is a CACHE qualification. The childcare industry widely respects CACHE qualifications;<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/cache\">see the courses available here</a>\n<h2><strong>Work experience</strong></h2>\nWork experience is hugely important, because it shows practical evidence of a students commitment to your long term goals. Furthermore, it also provides the student with hands-on learning to complement your study. As a result, it will give you an advantage when applying for jobs or university and you will probably enjoy getting stuck in to the practical side of working with children. Volunteering in a nursery or school, helping at a youth club and even working as a volunteerat a children\'s hospital, can give you experience and help decide the path you want to take.\n<h2><strong>Checks when working with children</strong></h2>\nThe majority of jobs that work with children require a Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check. This ensures these vulnerable groups are protected from people who have harmed, or posed a risk tochildren and consequently are unsuitable to work with them.<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/disclosure-and-barring-service\">Further information can be found here</a>\n<h2>Into the workplace</h2>\nWorking with children is great fun and as a result never dull. With such a large selection of careers on offer, study in this areacan always be put to good use. Working with children provides a rewarding and life enhancing experience.',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-10-12 15:52:34','2017-10-12 15:52:34',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=7611',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
