	(1409,'Samantha Rutter Joins Education Awards Judging Panel','samantha-rutter-education-awards-judging',NULL,NULL,'Open Study College are very proud to announce that our very own COO, Samantha Rutter, has been chosen to join the judging panel at the Education Awards 2018!\n<h2>What are the Education Awards?</h2>\nBased in Birmingham, The Education Awards returns for it?s second year after a very successful first year. The awards celebrates establishments who\'ve made an outstanding contribution to education, and those who have made a difference in the industry. Head over to their <a href=\"http://www.education-awards.co.uk/\">website</a>to find out more.\n\nIn July 2017 Open Study College was named Further Education College of the Year at the first Education Awards ceremony. It was an incredible to receive recognition of that kind, and we were very proud to win the award. So naturally, Open Study College were keen to be involved in the 2018 awards.\n<h2>Samantha?s Judging Role</h2>\nWith a total of sixteen categories to judge at the Education Awards 2018, the role of a judge isn\'t easy. Samantha, along with the rest of the judging panel, will need to whittle down the nomination entries to decide who should be shortlisted for the awards. It\'s brilliant that Open Study College have Samantha to represent us on the judging panel at the 2018 awards. We\'re sureshe will do a fantastic job!\n\nHere\'s what Samantha has to say about her forthcoming judging role:\n<blockquote>?I?m thrilled to be on the judging panel at the Education Awards 2018. I?m looking forward to seeing the nominations and learning more about the organisations involved. There will be some difficult but exciting decisions to be made when it comes to the finalists and winners as I?m anticipating the entries will all be very impressive!?</blockquote>',NULL,NULL,9,'2017-12-01 15:45:06','2017-12-01 15:45:06',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=7766',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
