	(1426,'Boost your accounting skills with an AAT Level 2 course','boost-accounting-skills-aat-level-2',NULL,NULL,'If you?re already an accountant, you will understand the requirements necessary in order to be successful and further your career. And if not, you might want to listen carefully?\n\nAccounting is not for the faint-hearted. It requires hours of study, countless exams and a strong determination to succeed. But we promise you the rewards are worth it.\n\nIf this sounds like you and something you?d be interested in, then you need to start somewhere. So we recommend starting with an <strong><u>AAT Foundation Certificate in Accounting Level 2</u></strong> course.\n\nAnd here?s why?\n<h2><strong>It covers all the basics and more</strong></h2>\nWith five detailed units, the AAT Level 2 course covers all the basics of accounting and more:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Bookkeeping Transactions</li>\n 	<li>Bookkeeping Controls</li>\n 	<li>Element of Costing</li>\n 	<li>Work Effectively in Finance</li>\n 	<li>Using Accounts Software</li>\n</ul>\nThis course teaches you about finance, communication, accountancy and business; from basic knowledge in-depth analysis and practical employment.\n<h2><strong>Internationally Recognised</strong></h2>\nProfessionally-developed by AAT, this Level 2 Certificate is a highly sought-after qualification by many accounting professional bodies. It demonstrates a dedication and commitment to accounting that employers look for when hiring, and will therefore boost your employability and earning potential.\n<h2><strong>Earning and Career Potential</strong></h2>\nThere are several career paths that this AAT Level 2 course can lead you down; from an accounts administrator to an accounts payable clerk, an accounting technician or even a finance assistant ? the choice is yours!\n\nWith multiple qualifications and years of experience and studying, your earning potential could grow indefinitely. For example, chartered accounts with multiple qualifications can 