	(1463,'How to Succeed with Your New Year\'s Resolution','succeed-new-years-resolution',NULL,NULL,'We?re onto our 2<sup>nd</sup> day of the New Year.\n\nHow many of you have already considered giving up on your new year\'s resolution and <em>?starting again on Monday?</em>??\n\n365 days may seem like a long time, but just think about it ? you are already 2 days down without realising!\n\nJust in case that isn?t enough motivation, think about this: imagine this exact day last year in 2017.\n<ul>\n 	<li>Were you disappointed or proud of yourself for what you had achieved in 2016?</li>\n 	<li>Did you wish you had put more effort into keeping up with your resolution?</li>\n</ul>\nNow think about this exact day next year in 2019:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Do you want to be in the exact same position you are now?</li>\n 	<li>Are you going to be proud of yourself and what you have achieved?</li>\n</ul>\nSeems like pretty obvious answers, right?\n\nSo let?s make a start on it from now. We want to help you to succeed with your ?New Year, New Me? mantra, and make sure you are in a much better position this time next year.\n<h2>Let?s think about the term \'New Year\'s Resolution\'</h2>\nThere is always a big focus on New Year\'s resolutions and the phrase \'New Year, New Me\'.\n\nBut if you think about it, it isn?t a new you. It?s just an improved version of you...\n\nIt will be the current you who makes all these changes.\n\nIt will be the current you who notices the difference.\n\nAnd it will be the current you who will be disappointed if thenew you doesn?t succeed.\n\nThis current you must be pretty good already if it can do all of that. So don?t put so much pressure on yourself.\n\nAcknowledging that there is room for improvement is a big step in itself. But don?t take an even bigger one backwards by stopping every time you mess up. That is all part of the process.\n\nThe secret to success is by recognising the version of yourself right now; appreciate where you are in life and what you have achieved. Then anything you do from this point onward will be a bonus.\n<h2>Let\'s start with your career</h2>\nPart of your resolution may be to get a new job or a promotion. But that isn?t going to happen overnight.\n\nStart by improving your knowledge and abilities and the rest will follow.\n\nAt Open Study College, we are here to help. Our distance learning courses are the first step towards succeeding with your New Year?s resolution. Provided by accredited organisations, they look widen your knowledge, boost your CV and improve your career prospects.\n\nWith tutor support and our professional team of student advisers, we will be here with you throughout your study journey to help you succeed.\n\nAnd with a year to complete, our courses are tailored around you to be completed in your own time, at your own pace from the comfort of your own home.\n\nCheck out our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/pages/how-it-works.html\">website</a> for full details of our courses and how to enrol, or call our Student Adviser team on<strong>03300 563100</strong> to start working towards your New Year\'s resolution today.',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-01-02 14:58:57','2018-01-02 14:58:57',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=7879',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
