	(1494,'How to Become a Nail Technician in Your Spare Time','nail-technician-spare-time',NULL,NULL,'With the constant demands and struggles of day-to-day life, it can be hard to fit in hobbies around this.\n\nBut it is because of these demands and struggles that it is <em>important </em>to fit in these hobbies. Having recreational time and doing things that you enjoy are what keep up all from breaking down or not being able to cope (we\'ve all been there).\n\nEven better than that: what if you were able to do something that you love <em>AND</em> make it into your career??\n<h2><strong>Become a Nail Technician in Your Spare Time</strong></h2>\nIf you love all things nails, then becoming a Nail Technician is just for you.\n\nThe role of a nail technician includes:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Treating nails to keep them healthy</li>\n 	<li>Filing, shaping and buffing nails</li>\n 	<li>Painting and decorating nails</li>\n</ul>\nNot only this, but there are certain personal traits that you must have in order to be successful. These include:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Friendly and approachable</li>\n 	<li>Organised</li>\n 	<li>Patient</li>\n 	<li>Creative</li>\n</ul>\nIf this sounds like you then it is easy to use these skills, invest in your hobby and earn some extra money in your spare time. Not only can you study in your own time at your own pace, but once you start, you will be able to work around your existing commitments; tailor your new hobby around you.\n\nDistance learning is made for situations like this; if you are currently working a full-time job or have daily commitments then your spare time is the perfect opportunity to work towards something you love.\n\nAt Open Study College, we have a selection of knowledge-based, distance learning courses that will suit your needs and career outcomes:\n<h3><strong>Nail Technician Level 3</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>This course is available to people of all abilities as no prior knowledge is needed to enrol. It covers the basics theories of health an