	(1540,'How We Can Help Boost Your Salary','boost-your-salary',NULL,NULL,'Wecould all do with a bit more money, right??\n\nYou may be doing fine with your current salary, but wouldn?t it be better to havemore spare money??\n\nFor that summer holiday? or to fix the hole in the roof? or just to treat yourself?\n\nWell we want to help you boost your salary so that all of this is possible. And here?s how:\n<h2><strong>Research</strong></h2>\nIt?s all well and good wanting a pay rise but knowing how much to ask for and why you deserve it is a big part of the battle.\n\nYou may be applying for a new job or simply asking for a pay increase at your current job; either way it is important to have some backup knowledge to support your claim to boost your salary.\n<ul>\n 	<li>Research your role in other companies and what salary they are offering</li>\n 	<li>Write down why you think you deserve a salary boost ? what you bring to the company, how you have worked hard etc.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Make yourself indispensable</strong></h2>\nIf you are a great asset to your workplace, it is unlikely that they will be willing to give you up. Losing you willbe worth more than the increase in your salary.\n\nEnsure that you are working to your maximum potential and in such a way that no one else would be able to do. A great way to do this is by improving your skills.\n\nHaving a vast catalogue of skills and qualifications under your belt will make you stand out to future employers. Taking up a qualification or course while you are in employment also shows your employer that you are committed and passionate about your role.\n\nAt Open Study College, we can help make this possible. We have a vast range of courses to improve your knowledge, skills and qualifications.\n\nFor example, if you work in Accounting or Bookkeeping, our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/aat\"><strong><u>AAT courses</u></strong></a> are a great way to improve skills and gain an internationally recognised qualification.\n\nOr childcare and education. We have a range of <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/cache\"><strong><u>CACHE courses</u></strong></a> that teach you the basics, as well as more detailed knowledge and practices for working with children and young people.\n\nEven if your career is a bit more obscure, like <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/dog-grooming.html\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"><strong>Dog Grooming</strong></span></a> or <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/cake-making-2.html\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"><strong>Cake Baking</strong></span></a>, there will be a course available to you.\n\nImprove your skills. Boost Your Salary.\n\nFor more information, check out our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/pages/how-it-works.html\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"><strong>website</strong></span></a>. Alternatively, you can give our Student Adviser team a call on<strong>03300 563100</strong> to discuss your options and enrol today!',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-01-29 11:56:22','2018-01-29 11:56:22',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=8056',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
