	(1549,'IAB Bookkeeping Courses - your path to success','iab-bookkeeping-courses',NULL,NULL,'Want to become a qualified bookkeeper?\n\nBecoming a bookkeeper is a long and winding road that is not to be attempted lightly.\n\nIt requires dedication, time and skills to be able to complete the necessary courses and examinations. It may seem daunting but, for those who are committed, it is extremely worth it.\n\nWe want to help you get there; and we think that one of the best ways of doing so is by studying one of the IAB Bookkeeping courseshere with us at Open Study College.\n<h2><strong>Step One: Find out about IAB</strong></h2>\nIAB (International Association of Bookkeepers) is a recognised association for qualified bookkeepers and small businesses, both internationally and in the UK.\n\nAllowing you to work within the industry, they offer a selection of courses and examinations to help you to become a qualified accountant or bookkeeper.\n<h2><strong>Step Two: Find out whether you are right for the job</strong></h2>\nAnyone can choose to become an accountant or bookkeeper. However, there are some specifications and pre-requisites that you will need to fulfil before being able to start.\n\nMost bookkeeping courses will require:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Basic to advanced numeracy skills (depending on the level)</li>\n 	<li>Basic literacy skills</li>\n 	<li>Prior knowledge of bookkeeping terminology and concepts</li>\n</ul>\n?and of course, a passion for the profession would come in handy.\n<h2><strong>Step Three:</strong> <strong>Choose the right course for you</strong></h2>\nWe offer a selection of courses that will help you get to where you want to be.\n\nWhether you are a beginner who is just getting into it and wants to improve their knowledge, or you are already on the ladder to success, you will find a course that suits you. For example:\n<ul>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/iab-manual-bookkeeping-level-1.html\">IAB Level 1 Award In Bookkeeping</a></