ral, detailed course on starting your own business ? either way, we have got you covered.\n\nOur <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/starting-your-own-business.html\"><strong><u>Starting Your Own Business Level 3</u></strong></a> course is a perfect place to start. It covers the basics of starting a business from planning to marketing and customers.\n\nAlternatively, we have combined courses that include both information on the industry and how to start a business. For example:\n<ul>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/garden-design-and-starting-your-own-business-3.html\">Garden Design and Starting Your Own Business</a></li>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/nutrition-start-business.html\">Nutrition Consultant and Starting Your Own Business</a></li>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/nail-technician-start-business-3.html\">Nail Technician Level 3 and Starting Your Own Business Level 3</a></li>\n</ul>\nThere are loads to choose from!\n\nCheck out our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/pages/how-it-works.html\">website</a> or give or Student Adviser team a call on<strong>03300 563100</strong> to discuss your options today!',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-02-08 11:52:18','2018-02-08 11:52:18',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/8108-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(1571,'Georgie Moseley from Help Harry Help Others visits our pop-up shop','georgie-hhho-open-study-college',NULL,NULL,'Georgie Moseley, from Birmingham-based charity Help Harry Help Others, dropped by to say hello to us at our pop-up shop.\n\nThe pop-up shop, at Birmingham\'s Bullring, was launched this week as part of our #StudyYourWay campaign, and is driving awareness of studying online, at your own pace with Open Study College.\n\nSince the beginning of the year we\'ve been working with our staff and students to raise money for Help Harry Help Others.\n\nHelp Harry Help Others was founded in 2009 by Harry Moseley, aiming to help support those with cancer and their families. Harry was 11 years old when he was diagnosed with a terminal brain tumour but did everything he could to help others in similar situations, and encourage others to join his journey to do the same.\n\nIt?s the familiar beaded bracelets that Harry created to raise money that the charity is well-known for. Identified as ?unique bracelets hand made with love for all people with cancer?, Open Study College wears these with pride and continues to promote all the hard work that Help Harry Help Others does.\n\nGeorgie Moseley, Harry\'s mother, continues to run the charity and push forward its initiative.\n\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-lang=\"en\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Great to stop by and see our charity supporter <a href=\"https://twitter.com/OpenStudyColl?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@OpenStudyColl</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/popupshop?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#popupshop</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Bullring?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@Bullring</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/StudyYourWay?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#StudyYourWay</a> here until 18th Feb so if your interested in <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/DistanceLearning?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#DistanceLearning</a>  do drop by <a href=\"https://t.co/496DRvlVZL\">pic.twitter.com/496DRvlVZL</a></p>&mdash; harry&#39;s mom #HHHO (@harry_moseley) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/harry_moseley/status/961615002699431936?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">February 8, 2018</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n\n<a href=\"http://hhho.org.uk/\" class=\"blog-cta\">Find out more about Help Harry Help Others</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-02-09 11:06:06','2018-02-09 11:08:30',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=8112',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(1572,'','8112-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Having launched its first pop-up shop this week as part of its ever-growing marketing campaign, Open Study College is using this opportunity to continue its work with independent charity, Help Harry Help Others.\n\nHelp Harry Help Others is a local charity that was founded in 2009 by Harry Moseley, aiming to help support those with cancer and their families. Being diagnosed with a terminal brain tumour encouraged Harry to do all he could to help others in similar situations, and encourage others to join his journey to do the same.\n\nIt?s the familiar beaded bracelets that Harry created to raise money that the charity is well-known for. Identified as ?unique bracelets hand made with love for all people with cancer?, Open Study College wears these with pride and continues to promote all the hard work that Help Harry Help Others does.\n\nGeorgie Moseley, mother of Harry Moseley, continues to run the charity and push forward its initiative. In doing so, she works closely with us at Open Study College, and we were delighted to have her attend our pop-up shop today to support us in this endeavour.\n<blockquote>[Quote from Georgie?]</blockquote>\nSince the start of 2018, Open Study College and its students have been following Harry?s initiative and continuing the success by donating to the independent charity with every new course enrolment.\n<blockquote>[QUOTE FROM Steven?]</blockquote>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-02-08 12:43:33','2018-02-08 12:43:33',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/8112-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(1573,'Choosing the Right Distance Learning Course for You','choosing-distance-learning-course',NULL,NULL,'There are 3 key factors when deciding which distance learning course is right for you:\n<ol>\n 	<li>The course</li>\n 	<li>The level or grade</li>\n 	<li>The course provider</li>\n</ol>\nFor most people, studying will have a large impact on their lives, so it is important that these decisions are thought out carefully in order to make the right choice for you.\n<h2><strong>The Course</strong></h2>\nThis is the most important part of the process. You are paying for this course, and once you have it, there may be no going back.\n\nEnsure that you choose a course that you are interested in. Otherwise you will not be passionate enough about the course to finish it. People tend to learn best when they <em>want</em> to learn about what they are studying.\n\nIn addition, if you are using this course to further your education or career, you will need to ensure that the course you choose will be able to do this. There is very little point in studying a Mathematics course if you want to become a Personal Trainer?\n<h2><strong>The Level/Grade </strong></h2>\nSimilarly to the choice of course, you will need to choose wisely if you plan for this to further your career or education.\n<ul>\n 	<li>What level/grade are you at now?</li>\n 	<li>Where do you need to get to?</li>\n 	<li>Will a specific level/grade help you more than others?</li>\n</ul>\nThese are all questions you should ask yourself when deciding on the right level/grade to study.\n\nFor example, in order to get into university you will need to achieve UCAS points; these are attainable through studying A-Levels so this would be the correct choice for you.\n<h2><strong>The Course Provider</strong></h2>\nFinally, is the where/who to study with.\n\nWhen choosing a distance learning course provider, you want to ensure that you are studying with an establishment that has your best interests at heart. For the duration of your course, you will be turning to them for any help and support that you may need; you need to be able to trust and have faith in them.\n\nThis is the easiest choice of them all?\n\nOpen Study College are an award-winning distance learning course provider with over 60,000 students already enrolled. When you enrol with us, you will receive:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Award-winning tutor support</li>\n 	<li>The choice to study online or via a course pack</li>\n 	<li>A professional and friendly Student Support team</li>\n 	<li>A choice of over 450 courses to choose from</li>\n 	<li>Accredited qualifications such as CACHE, AAT and Active IQ</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>PLUS,</strong> as a handy perk, you will also receive a <strong>FREE</strong> NUS Extra card to use for the duration of your course.\n\nSo at least one part is sorted. Now it?s just time to sort out the others?\n\nIf you need some help deciding, give our Student Adviser team a call on <strong>03300 563100</strong>. Or check out our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/pages/how-it-works.html\">website</a> to see which course is right for you.',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-02-09 09:54:09','2018-02-09 09:56:43',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=8116',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
