	(1584,'Open Study College Shortlisted at FSB West Midlands Awards','open-study-college-shortlisted-fsb-west-midlands-awards',NULL,NULL,'We\'re excited to announce that Open Study College has been shortlisted for two awards at the FSB West Midlands Awards:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Family Business of the Year</li>\n 	<li>Digital Business of the Year</li>\n</ul>\nFollowing the success of our 10<sup>th</sup> anniversary year, we are delighted to be continuing this success into 2018.\n<h2><strong>The FSB West Midlands Awards 2018</strong></h2>\nThe <a href=\"https://fsbawards.co.uk/\">Federation of Small Businesses Awards</a> celebrates the best of small businesses throughout the UK, providing great recognition and pride across chosen sectors. The award winners are chosen by expert judges who take hard work, originality and success into account when deciding.\n\nOpen Study College have been shortlisted for Family Business of the Year and Digital Business of the Year within the West Midlands area, and we could not be more delighted.\n\nMany companies take pride in being shortlisted for and winning an FSB Celebrating Small Business Award. It showcases the hard work and success that may not have been otherwise recognised within the community.\n\nSamantha Rutter, COO of Open Study College, had this to say about being shortlisted for the award:\n<blockquote><em>?We could not be more pleased and honoured to be shortlisted for these awards. It\'s overwhelming to continue the success of our 10<sup>th</sup> anniversary year, and to be recognised within the community for our continued hard work. We are amongst some worthy competition so to even be shortlisted is an achievement in itself for Open Study College.? </em></blockquote>\nThis event will be held on 16<sup>th</sup> March 2018 at the National Conference Centre, Birmingham; the winners of each category will then be entered into the National Finals, which will take place on 3<sup>rd</sup> May 2018 at Westminster Park Plaza, London.\n\nA