	(1613,'How to Get That Promotion','8189-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Are you long overdue a promotion?\n\nSometimes people get comfortable in their current role that they never think to ask for a promotion.\n\nOr in other cases, some people are longing for a promotion, but are unsure how to go about getting it.\n\nHere?s how we at Open Study College can help you get that promotion:\n<h2><strong>Do your homework</strong></h2>\nNot so much in the literal sense? (but if you do have homework to do then that would be a great start in impressing your boss.)\n\nIt?s fine to want and think you deserve a promotion, but it is convincing your employer that\'s the hard part.\n\nWhether it is a natural step up with a slight change in title, or advancing into a completely new but better role, you need to know about the job you are asking for; why do you fit the bill?\n<ul>\n 	<li>Research the role and what it entails</li>\n 	<li>Look at what qualities you have that would fit the role</li>\n 	<li>Think of what the role lacks and how you would improve it</li>\n 	<li>Check if there is a position available. If not, suggest it</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Become irreplaceable </strong></h2>\nThose who present more value within their workplace are unlikely to be overlooked by higher level management. If you are that great within the company, it would only make sense to promote you to improve the company overall.\n\nBefore applying for a promotion, ensure that you are performing to your highest potential in your current role. You need to be doing this in a manner that no one else would be able to do as well as you.\n<h2><strong>Make sure you fit the promotion</strong></h2>\nThinking you can do a role and actually being capable of it are two different things; you need to ensure that your skills and knowledge are fit for purpose.\n\nIn addition, studying in your spare time shows initiative and lets your employer know that you are serious about your job and this promotion.\n\nAt Open Study College