erage salary for a Physicist is 34,000!\n\n&nbsp;\n<ul>\n 	<li>Wide range of career options</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nIf you?re anything like us, when you think of a role within the Physics industry, you automatically think of becoming a Scientist. And although The Big Bang Theory sitcom has made this more popular in recent times, this is not the only career available.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nMany people who study Physics go onto becoming teachers, engineers, analysts or even a criminologist. As Physics promotes a wide range of skills, your A Level Physics course could take you in a multitude of directions.\n\n&nbsp;\n<ul>\n 	<li>Earn while you learn</li>\n</ul>\nAs the number of people who study Physics is decreasing, some facilities offer grants and bursaries to those who wish to take up the subject.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nOr if that isn?t the case, our A Level course is developed to be studied through home learning, so you can fit it in around your work and personal life.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThink you?ve got what it takes to be the next Sheldon Cooper or Brian Cox?\n\n&nbsp;\n\nEnrol onto our A Level Physics course and start your journey today.',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-03-16 10:21:48','2018-03-16 10:21:48',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/8285-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
