	(1689,'Careers Advice - How to Become a Travel Agent','8329-revision-v1',NULL,NULL,'Are you one of those people who spend most of their time looking up holidays, flights and new destinations?\n\nAnd when you are on a holiday you are already planning where to go next?\n\nSame.\n\nWell that?s basically the life of a Travel Agent. The only difference is that they receive a salary for it at the end of the month.\n\nThat sounds much better than just doing it for fun!\n<h2><strong>What is a Travel Agent?</strong></h2>\nA Travel Agent is someone who book holidays for customers, researching the best deals and planning all the little details of their trip to ensure they make the most of their time.\n\nThe usual day-to-day duties and routine of a Travel Agent includes:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Communicating with customers to get the information they need, i.e. budget, destination ideas, type of holiday etc.</li>\n 	<li>Comparing holidays for the best deals ? this will include transport, accommodation, activities etc.</li>\n 	<li>Ensuring they know about the rules and regulations of travelling to certain countries including visas, insurance and vaccinations</li>\n 	<li>Being a point of contact for customers while they are away</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Is there any career progression?</strong></h2>\nThere are degrees within Travel Agency that can determine your salary and career progression.\n\n<strong>Travel Agent</strong> ? those who work in branches have the capabilities to be promoted. This is often due to commission and sales. Depending on experience, these roles can earn anything up to 25,000!\n\n<strong>Branch Manager</strong> ? these are the people who are in control of all the goings on within a specific Travel Agency site or branch. Their role includes the duties of a Travel Agent, with the added responsibility of ensuring that everyone is doing their job and that everything is going to plan. These can earn anything up to 30,000!\n\n<strong>Tour Manager</strong> ? this type of Travel Agent is responsible for the organisation of a specific tour holiday or trip. This may include sports club holidays abroad, or general community tours ? every little detail is your responsibility. They may have more responsibility, but they also have more fun as they often get to go on the trip themselves and can earn anything up to 40,000!\n<h2><strong>How do I become a Travel Agent?</strong></h2>\nLuckily for you, a degree or specific qualification is not completely <em>necessary</em> in order to become a Travel Agent.\n\nManyemployers offer training, but personality and experience play a good part in helping with your career prospects.\n\nHowever, some form of studying will give you that boost and competitive edge that you need and help you take that first step into the industry.\n\nFor example, our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/igcse-travel-tourism.html\">iGCSE Travel and Tourism</a>.\n\nThis course gives you the same qualification that you would receive in school and uncovers the main responsibilities and subjects that you need to become a Travel Agent.\n\nOr the <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/ncfe-tourism-management-course.html\">Tourism Management Level 3</a> course provides you with the skills to become a Tour Manager directly, pinpointing all the responsibilities that you will face.\n\nBut if you?re still not sure, we have more courses available on our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/travel-tourism_courses.html\">website</a>.\n\nOr call <strong>03300 563100</strong> to speak to one of our student advisers who can help you choose the right course to put you on track to becoming a Travel Agent, today!',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-03-27 10:14:20','2018-03-27 10:14:20',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/8329-revision-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(1690,'How Distance Learning Can Boost Your CV','distance-learning-boost-your-cv',NULL,NULL,'Starting a new or progressing in your current career isn?t an easy task.\n\nWith the number of jobs decreasing and the unemployment rate rising, the route to employment has a few more bumps in the road than in previous years.\n\nIt is not just enough to be good at your job. You need to show that you are <em>better</em> than anyone else that can also do your job.\n\nYour CV is the key. This is the first impression that employers will have, so you need to ensure that it?s a great one.\n\nAmongst other things, distance learningcan help boost your CV and help you to stand out from the crowd.\n<h2><strong>Post-Graduate or Extra-Curricular Learning</strong></h2>\nStudyingafter university or in your spare time to improve your career shows a passion for your industry. It reveals that it\'s not just a way to make money, but your hobby and what you want to do with your life. Those who enjoy what they do are usually the ones who do it the best!\n<h2><strong>Accredited Qualifications</strong></h2>\nNot only are our courses bench-marked to ensure they provide the required knowledge that employers desire, some are also accredited by internationally-known organisations. Such as<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/cache\">CACHE</a>, <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/aat\">AAT</a> and <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/active-iq\">Active IQ</a> just to name a few. Adding these to your CV puts you ahead of your competition and prove that you know what you are doing.\n<h2><strong>Work Experience</strong></h2>\nEmployers appreciate those who use their initiative to occupy their time with activities that are beneficial to their career. Rather than simply lounging around, you are making strides to better yourself. In addition, they need to know that you have had some practice and experience within your job, and that you know what you are doing.\n\nSome of our distance learning courses provide practical training or placement opportunities, so you will be able to expand your knowledge as well as your skills and experience ? and boost your CV at the same time!\n<h2><strong>CV Rewriting Service</strong></h2>\nIn addition to all that, we also offer a CV rewriting service once you have finished your course. Our experts redraft your CV to give you the best possible start in the search for your new career. We know how to make your new qualifications stand out and help you to impress your future employers.\n\nSo to get that head-start in life, take a look at our <span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"><a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/pages/how-it-works.html\">website</a></span> to find the perfect course for you. Or call our Student Adviser team on<strong>03300 563100</strong> to boost your CV today!',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-03-28 11:08:00','2018-03-28 11:08:00',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=8334',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL);
