	(1744,'Learn English Online with Open Study College','learn-english-online-open-study-college',NULL,NULL,'It seems like it has been all about languages lately.\n\nLast week it was Chinese Language Day, and today it is English Language Day.\n\nAnd what a day for it to fall on, as it is also St. George?s Day.\n\nSt. George was the patron saint of England who apparently killed a dragon and saved a princess?\n\nNow, we can?t help you with fighting any dragons, but we?ve got you covered when it comes to learning English.\n\nOver 375 million people speak English in the world, with those people lying across more than 50 countries. As such a popular language, it makes sense to learn English online to improve your ability as well as broaden your skill set.\n<h2><strong>Learn English Online</strong></h2>\nOur online English course is like no other. It allows you to improve your listening, reading and speaking skills all from the comfort of your own home!\n\nMaybe English is your second language and you want to improve your knowledge of the basics?\n\n?or perhaps you just want to freshen up your skills.\n\nEither way, learning online is the way to do it.\n\nWhen you learn English online, you are in control of your learning. So if you are struggling with certain aspects of the course, you can go over it as many times as you need to.\n\nIf in the future you find that some things have slipped your mind, you will have it there at your disposal to go over anything that you need refreshing.\n\nThis is more beneficial than learning with a tutor in person or in a class as you do not need to adjust to the pace of the other students, and you will have the materials there to look back on when you choose ? unlike a tutor.\n<h2><strong>Which courses are available?</strong></h2>\nAt Open Study College, we offer 2 online English courses that would be best to learn English online.\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/english-beginner-to-advanced.html\"><strong><u>English ? B