	(1786,'Ever wanted to learn Spanish? Here\'s your chance!','learn-spanish',NULL,NULL,'Many people often say they would like to learn a new language, but never commit themselves or find they don?t have the time.\n\nBut we say different: learning a language is one of the most rewarding things you can do for your life and your career.\n\nApparently English is one of the hardest languages to learn and, if you are reading this, you seem to have managed that. So another language should be a doddle.\n\nIn that case, why not learn Spanish?\n\nHere?s 4 reasons why we think you should learn Spanish.\n<h2><strong>Improves brain functions and activity </strong></h2>\nWhen your brain is challenged and has to cope with something more difficult than it is used to, it improves its functions.LearningSpanish will not only make it easier for you to learn other languages in the future, it will make learning in general that little bit simpler.\n\nIn addition, Spanish is one of the best languages to start with if you have never learnt a new language before, as there are\n<h2><strong>Travel and culture opportunities </strong></h2>\nThere are many countries all over the world that speak Spanish.\n\nSpain?Peru?Dominican Republic?Mexico?Cuba? the list could go on.\n\nWhether you want to get up close and personal with sea turtles in the Galapagos Islands, or see the Sagrada Famlia in Barcelona, learning Spanish could help you get there. Speaking and understanding one of the most popular languages in the world will help you make the most of your travels.\n\nYou will be able to speak to the locals, ask for directions and understand what is going on around you; your travels will be so much better!\n<h2><strong>Career possibilites</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Spanish teacher</li>\n 	<li>Translator</li>\n 	<li>TEFL teacher</li>\n</ul>\n?these are just a few of the most popular job roles that people who learn Spanish take on. But if you think about it, you could do any job you wanted? but do it in a Spanish-speaking country!\n\nHow amazing would it be to work abroad? Experiencing a new culture, new experiences while getting paid!\n<h2><strong>Boost your CV </strong></h2>\nSpeaking another language is like gold dust on CVs. Many employers look for this as it shows commitment to learning as well as benefits for the company. If a company has overseas communications, then it will need to hire someone who can work internationally for them.\n\nSo you know what this means? free (business) holidays!\n\nDoes this sound like something you?re interested in? Then check out our <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/linguaphone-spanish.html\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Spanish ? Beginner to Advanced course</strong></span></a>.\n\nThe Linguaphone method through distance learning ensures that you are in control.\n\nThis self-study course is completed with 6 audio CDs, a handbook and a textbook, and contains 3 fundamental elements to assist you through your learning:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Listening</li>\n 	<li>Understanding</li>\n 	<li>Speaking</li>\n</ul>\nTake a look at the course on our <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/pages/how-it-works.html\">website</a></strong></span>, or call our Student Adviser team on <strong>03300 563 100</strong> to enrol today!\n\nThat way, you can start planning what you?re going to do on those free (business) holidays?',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-05-25 10:55:18','2018-05-25 10:55:18',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=8483',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
