	(1791,'How to Become a Nutrition Consultant','become-nutrition-consultant',NULL,NULL,'Are you interested in food and food science?\n\nDo you want to help others to become healthy and lead better lives?\n\nThen you are the perfect fit to become a nutrition consultant.\n<h2><strong>What is a nutrition consultant? </strong></h2>\nIn laymen?s terms, a nutrition consultant lets people know what is good for them and what isn?t. Not just in general, but for specific needs and dietary requirements.\n\nFor example, a nutrition consultant may make a specific dietary plan for someone who is trying to lose weight. So, in combination with steady exercise, these food choices will benefit them and aid their weight loss.\n\nOr perhaps a diabetic. There are subtle sugars in everyday foods, so a nutrition consultant will know which foods to avoid and which will benefit.\n\nThe main duties of a nutrition consultant include:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Discussing dietary issues and developing eating plans</li>\n 	<li>Evaluating the pros and cons of foods</li>\n 	<li>Knowing the scientific terms and contents of food groups</li>\n 	<li>Working with clients, schools, hospitals and other settings</li>\n</ul>\nSalaries for a nutrition consultant can start from 20,000 and increase to around 50,000 with experience.\n<h2><strong>Which nutrition courses are available?</strong></h2>\nThere are no specific entry requirements to become a nutrition consultant in the UK. However, most nutrition consultants have knowledge and a qualification in the subject area.\n\nMany people take the route of A Levels, which then lead onto university in order to become a nutrition consultant. <strong><u>A-Level Biology</u></strong> would need to be one of your choices as it will benefit you to know more about the body and how it works.\n\nFor a list of all the A-Level courses we offer, visit our <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/a-level\"><strong>website</strong></a></span>.\n\nAnother route would be to learn through courses and work your way up from there. At Open Study College, we offer a variety of Nutrition courses provided by different organisations, such as:\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/understanding-nutrition-performance-healthy-eating-level-2-award.html\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Active IQ Level 2 Award in Understanding Nutrition Performance and Healthy Eating</strong></span></a>\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/nutrition-and-Health-cache.html\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>CACHE Level 2 Certificate in Nutrition and Health</strong></span></a>\n\nIn some cases, you may already be working in a career but need some nutritional knowledge to progress. For these instances, we provide course such as:\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/diet-nutrition-exercise-children.html\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Diet Nutrition and Exercise for Children</strong></span></a>\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/ncfe-nutrition-consultant.html\">Nutrition Consultant Level 3</a></strong></span>\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/sports-nutrition-3.html\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Sport Nutrition Level 3</strong></span></a>\n\nWith up to 34 courses regarding Diet Fitness and Nutrition, there is sure to be something to suit your personal career needs.\n\nVisit our website or contact our Student Adviser team on <strong>03300 563100</strong> and find out which Nutrition course is the right one for you.',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-05-21 10:11:48','2018-05-21 10:11:48',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=8490',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
