	(1806,'Ways to Improve Your Mental Health','improve-your-mental-health',NULL,NULL,'Mental health is a stigma that many of us may not like to talk about.\n\nBut just think about it: your brain is an organ.\n\nJust like any of your other organs, it can get sick or not function as well. Would we be ashamed to talk about having a heart attack?\n\nThen we shouldn?t be ashamed of talking about our mental health, either.\n<h3><strong>Did you know that 1 in 4 people have a mental health issue?</strong></h3>\nThat is a quarter of the entire population! Surely enough to be able to say that it is a relatively normal occurrence.\n\nSo there is no need to be ashamed.\n\nEspecially when there is so much help out there. Some things that you will need a specialist for, and others that you can do at home to help improve your mental health.\n<h2><strong>Ways to improve your mental health</strong></h2>\nLearning how to improve your mental health will reduce its impact on your life.\n\nSimple things like:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Participating in exercise</li>\n 	<li>Eliminating the initial cause</li>\n 	<li>Talking to friends/a professional</li>\n</ul>\nThese can make a big difference and considerably reduce the impact.\n\nMental health can deteriorate due to influencing factors within your life.\n\nFor example, someone may develop an eating disorder due to being bullied earlier in life. Or others may develop depression due to environmental factors.\n\nOf course, not all cases of mental health issues can be personally solved with small exercises, but there are simple things that you can do to help generally improve your mental health and help to keep you on the right track.\n<ul>\n 	<li>\n<h3><strong>Be nice to yourself</strong></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\nThere are enough people in the world who may choose not to be nice to you, so don?t make yourself one of them. You are the only you and the best you that you will ever know. Make sure you appreciate that.\n<ul>\n 	<li>\n<h3><strong>Remove any negativity from your life</strong></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\nWhether this be friends, jobs or any type of external factor, it is necessary to remove this from your life. These influences can get you down and have a large impact on your mental health.\n<ul>\n 	<li>\n<h3><strong>Set realistic goals</strong></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\nA large part of mental health is feeling inadequate or like a failure which can be cause by setting your sights too high. Start with realistic goals that you can gradually achieve. Even if you have to achieve 50 small goals before getting to where you want to be, it is better than setting a single unrealistic goal that will disappoint you if you fail.\n<ul>\n 	<li>\n<h3><strong>Don?t be afraid to ask for help</strong></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\nEveryone needs help every now and again ? it is nothing to be ashamed about. Take the time to talk to a friend, family member or professional when you need it. This can go a long way if you want to improve your mental health.\n\nMental health affects us all.\n\nIf we all do our best to keep on top of it, we can help ourselves in becoming calmer, less stressed and happier.',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-05-18 09:56:40','2018-12-03 10:12:39',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=8510',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
