 for those who are already on their way, this course enables you to learn about both financial aspects: accounting and bookkeeping in more detail.\n<h2><strong>Step Three: Tailor your CV for your career</strong></h2>\nAnyone can choose to become an accountant or bookkeeper. However, there are some specifications and pre-requisites that you will need to fulfil before being able to start.\n\nMost bookkeeping courses will require:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Basic to advanced numeracy skills (depending on the level)</li>\n 	<li>Basic literacy skills</li>\n 	<li>Prior knowledge of bookkeeping terminology and concepts</li>\n</ul>\n?and of course, a passion for the profession would come in handy.\n\nThese skills and qualities are all developed during the course but knowing how to present them to your future employers is part of the battle.\n\nOur FREE CV re-writing service does this for you. Our professional team are on hand to craft you the best CV to make you stand out from a crowd and achieve the bookkeeping career you desire.\n<h2><strong>Step Four: Helping you to enrol onto a course</strong></h2>\nIf you find a course and decide it is perfect for you, then click enrol online.\n\nAlternatively, give our Student Adviser team a call on <strong>03300 563100</strong> to hear more about the courses and your options.',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-05-29 10:43:09','2018-05-29 10:43:09',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=8534',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
