	(1858,'7 perfect jobs for those who love travelling','7-perfect-jobs-love-travelling',NULL,NULL,'Wanderlust refers to those who love travelling.\n\nThey have the urge to see the world and all it has to offer, while meeting new people, exploring new cultures and seeing new things.\n\nIdeally, we all would love to do this. But we can?t. We have to work.\n\nBut if there was a way to combine our passions for travelling with the necessity to work, there would be a lot more happy people in the world.\n<blockquote><em>?Choose a job you love, and you will never have to work a day in your life? -</em>Confucius</blockquote>\nIf you?re one of these people, then here?s a list of the perfect job choices that will allow you to work while living amidst your love of travelling.\n<ul>\n 	<li>\n<h3><strong>TEFL teacher </strong></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\nThese are in constant short supply. If your English language is of a good level and you can <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/languages_courses.html\"><strong><u>speak another language</u></strong></a>, travel to another country and help those across the world to improve their English skills.\n<ul>\n 	<li>\n<h3><strong>Blogger</strong></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\nIn the modern day, blogging is as popular as doctors and the health care service. And what?s more, you don?t need any qualifications or skills to become a blogger. Just let your mind and experiences tell the story.\n<ul>\n 	<li>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/cabin-crew-diploma.html\"><strong>Flight attendant</strong></a></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\nThis career speaks for itself. Travelling from country to country, exploring the world and meeting new people. (We hear the tips are pretty good, too!)\n<ul>\n 	<li>\n<h3><strong>Bartender</strong></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\nOne of the most versatile careers out there, you can be a bartender anywhere in the world. The skills are the same and cocktails are easy to pick up, too. We would suggest learning a few conversational phrases though to get you off the ground.\n<ul>\n 	<li>\n<h3><strong>Au pair</strong></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\nOne of the most rewarding jobs, becoming an au pair will give you a great foundation for travelling. In a lot of cases, you are provided with accommodation, you get to work with children, and on your off days you can explore the new and beautiful environment you are in.\n<ul>\n 	<li>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/hotel-hospitality-diploma.html\"><strong>Hospitality </strong></a></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\nJust like bartending, hospitality never goes out of style. Hotels are one of the world?s biggest incomes all over the world ? plus you never know who you might meet there?\n<ul>\n 	<li>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/digital-photography.html\"><strong>Photographer </strong></a></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\nTake pictures of the world in all its glory be becoming a photographer. Get paid to travel and snap ? most people do this anyway, so why not do it for a living?\n\nSound intriguing? Then don?t hesitate to start your dreams today. Talk to our student adviser team on <strong>03300 563 100 </strong>who can help you choose the best career route for you.',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-06-18 10:38:08','2018-09-27 10:54:37',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=8586',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
