	(1935,'What\'s Next? Other Options Post A Levels','other-options-alevels',NULL,NULL,'It?s the day after.\n\nYou?ve received your A Level results, good or bad, and now you?re planning your future. But who says that future needs to be the path that is pre-set for you?\n\nWhen we?re at school, we get told to do GCSEs, do A Levels, go to university and be successful; that?s a great route. But it?s not the only route that you can take. After your A Levels, there are other options that can get you to where you want to be and help you to become just as successful.\n<h2><strong>Other options that we offer</strong></h2>\n<h3><strong>Accounting and Bookkeeping</strong></h3>\nIf you want to work in finance as an accountant or bookkeeper, Open Study College have great partnerships with some of the leading organisations for accounting and bookkeeping, such as <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/iab\"><strong>IAB</strong></a>, <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/icb\"><strong>ICB </strong></a>and <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/aat\"><strong>AAT</strong></a>. These recognised qualifications vary from award to diploma levels and provide you with the valuable knowledge and practical skills that will allow you to become a qualified accountant or bookkeeper.\n<h3><strong>Care, Health and Education </strong></h3>\nWorking in health and childcare is one of the most popular careers of our generation. Working with <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/cache\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>CACHE</strong></span></a>, we offer a range of qualifications for the care and education industries. Covering areas such as <strong>teaching support</strong>, <strong>childcare</strong>, <strong>nutrition</strong>, and <strong>health and social care</strong>, these highly accredited qualifications will give you the skills you need to further your career.\n<h3><strong>Personal Training and Fitness</strong></h3>\nWant to be a Personal Trainer? A university degree isn?t your only option. Our courses from <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/qualifications/active-iq\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Active IQ</strong></span></a> - the UK?s leading organisation for vocational and active learning - provide professionally designed qualifications that promote careers in the active leisure and wellbeing sectors. Our course range includes <strong>fitness instruction</strong>, <strong>personal training</strong> and designing <strong>exercise programmes</strong>.\n<h2><strong>Why Choose Open Study College? </strong></h2>\nOpen Study College is one of the UK?s leading distance learning providers with over 11 years? worth of experience in the industry. During this time, more 73,000 students have furthered their education and developed their career prospects by studying a course or qualification with us.\n\nWith a varied range of qualifications, this way of studying offers endless opportunities to all students.\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong>Flexible &amp; Convenient</strong></li>\n 	<li><strong>Affordable Study</strong></li>\n 	<li><strong>Unlimited Tutor Support</strong></li>\n 	<li><strong>Student Perks</strong></li>\n</ul>\nDon?t think you have to follow the same path that has been paved for you; you are more than capable of paving your own.\n\nIf you need any more information or help with choosing your options, call our student adviser team on <strong>03300 563 100</strong> who will be more than happy to help. Or head over to our website to see all the qualifications and courses that can help your career.\n\n<strong><a class=\"blog-cta\" href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/pages/how-it-works.html\">Take a look at our courses</a>  </strong>',NULL,NULL,9,'2018-08-17 09:32:12','2018-08-17 09:32:12',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=8764',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL);
