	(2060,'How a veterinary assistant course kickstarted Laila\'s career','veterinary-assistant-course-lailas-career',NULL,NULL,'After finishing college, Laila, decided to pursue her dream career and study a veterinary assistant course. Since finishing her veterinary assistant course with Open Study College, Laila has started a new position as a veterinary care assistant. Here?s Laila?s story and how she succeeded on her distance learning journey?\n<h3><strong>What?s your background in terms of education/career?</strong></h3>\nPrior to studying my level 3 veterinary support assistant course with Open Study College, I spent 2 years at a college studying a level 2 animal care diploma. Alongside being at college, I had a part-time job working as a dog grooming assistant. This allowed me to have a hands-on approach and to gain practical skills that I would be needing for a future dedicated to working with animals.\n<h3><strong>What made you want to study your chosen subject?</strong></h3>\nAlthough I loved dog grooming, I knew it wasn?t the right career path for me. I have always wanted to work within a veterinary practice. It has been my dream for as long as I can remember and thanks to Open Study College my dream became a reality.\n<h3><strong>What was your motivation for studying?</strong></h3>\nI like to live by the quote ?the expert in anything was once a beginner?. This helped me to motivate myself, even when I thought I was never going to achieve my goal.\n<h3><strong>Why did you choose distance learning over traditional study methods?</strong></h3>\nI chose distance learning over traditional studying methods as it allows you study from the comfort of your own home. I believe that a classroom is not for everybody and, therefore, studying in a classroom will not be as effective. As someone who found school challenging, I definitely recommend distance learning to anyone who is also struggling/has struggled.\n<h3><strong>Why did you choose to study with Open Study College?</strong></h3>\nI chose Open Study College as I know that when you sign up to your course, you are assigned a tutor that it available to help you every step of the way. They are only ever an email away. I also chose Open Study College because there are no strict guidelines, this allowed me to balance a job whilst studying.\n<h3><strong>What have you enjoyed most about your studies?</strong></h3>\nI have enjoyed the wide range of topics involved in my assignments, it has allowed me to broaden my horizons.\n<h3><strong>What do you plan to do with your course after completing your studies?</strong></h3>\nIt is with great thanks to Open Study College and the wonderful tutor that I was assigned, that I am now in my first ever ?veterinary care assistant? job. I plan on using my knowledge that I have gained through completing this course and applying it whilst working in a veterinary practice.\n<h3><strong>Do you plan to study any further in the future?</strong></h3>\nSome day in the future I would like to progress my role and become a veterinary nurse.\n<h3><strong>Is there anything else you?d like to add?</strong></h3>\nThank you! I would recommend this course and this college to anyone I know that is planning to study.\n\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/courses/veterinary-support-assistant\">Click here if you\'d love to find out more about our veterinary support assistant course.</a>',NULL,NULL,9,'2019-03-07 09:08:48','2019-03-07 09:08:48',2,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=9046',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
