ing-courses\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">our website</a>.\n\nPrefer to speak to someone?\n\nCall our team of student advisers on 03300 563100 ? they?ll be happy to chat through your options and help you on the first or next step to your future in accountancy.',NULL,NULL,9,'2019-04-24 11:11:48','2019-04-24 11:11:48',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/9151-autosave-v1/',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
	(2099,'Accountancy trivia - enjoy these 5 fun facts!','accountancy-trivia-enjoy-5-fun-facts',NULL,NULL,'Trivia is a great conversation filler when things get awkward, and even better when it involves little known facts. Perfect for the dinner table, a party, or just to impress your friends or colleagues, let us share some accountancy trivia with you!\n<h2>Forever blowing bubbles</h2>\nAn accountant invented bubblegum! Walter Diemar worked for the Fleer Chewing Gum Company in Philadelphia. For years the company had been searching for a less sticky formula which would enable bubbles to be blown. In 1928 Diemer was testing recipes and found a suitable one. It was marketed as Dubble Bubble and sales surpassed $1.5m in the first year! It was bright pink in colour because that was the only dye he had to hand at the time. In order to help sell the product, Diemer himself taught sales people how to blow bubbles, so they could pass the ?skill? on to potential customers.\n<h2>Scarface</h2>\nIt was accountants who brought down Chicago crime boss Al Capone. One of the most notorious American gangsters of the 20<sup>th</sup>Century and the inspiration behind scores of film and TV productions; Capone had a suspected crime sheet covering everything from bootlegging to murder. But it was a conviction for tax evasion that would ultimately put a stop to his criminal activity and land him in jail.\n<h2>Double O, double B, double K</h2>\nBookkeeper and the words derived from it (bookkeeping etc.) are the only words in the English language with 3 consecutive sets of double letters. You?re trying to think of others now, aren?t you? Think away, you won?t find any!\n<h2>And the winner is...</h2>\nEver wondered who counts up the votes to give us the Academy Award winners in the annual Oscars? It?s a team of accountants. Every year since the 1930s accountants have counted, recounted and counted again to ensure the accuracy of the votes placed. With over 6,000 Academy members eligible to vote, plus a published nomination list followed by announcing the final winners, that?s a lot of counting! You may remember a couple of years ago that the wrong winner was announced in the best picture category, due to a mix up. Think you could do a better job?<a href=\"https://www.beancounters.co.uk/categories/accounting\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Study an accounting course with Beancounters</a>and who knows what the future may hold!\n<h2>A brief history lesson</h2>\nAccounting, in a crude form, dates back thousands of years. Records dating back more than 7,000 years have been found in the Middle East. These records show lists of expenditure, and goods received and traded.\n\nHow many of those accountancy trivia facts did you know?\n<h2>Feeling inspired?</h2>\n<a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/bookkeeping-courses\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Browse our accounting courses!</a>\n\nNot sure how distance learning works? <a href=\"https://www.openstudycollege.com/how-it-works\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Click here to find out more</a>.\n\nPrefer to speak to someone? Call us on 03300 563100.\n\n&nbsp;',NULL,NULL,9,'2019-05-15 11:08:10','2019-05-15 11:08:10',1,'https://blog.openstudycollege.com/?p=9160',1,1,1,0,0,NULL,NULL),
